title: rice with grapes(a cold dish)
directions: Boil the rice. Cover with a tea towel. Replace the lid, and let pot sit for 20 minutes. Fluff rice with two forks and put in a bowl. Again cover with a towel for 30 minutes.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Prepare eggplant.
Peel and slice.
Soak in salt water for 1 hour.
Drain and dry with paper towel.
Shake in bag of flour. Dip in Golden Fry Batter, then place in hot fat until golden brown.

title: apricot-glazed ham slice
directions: Place ham on microproof serving dish; set aside.
Combine marmalade, raisins, paprika and nutmeg in 1 c. glass measure. Cook on HI for 1 minute.
Spoon sauce over ham slice and cook on 70 for 3 1/2-5 minutes, depending on thickness of ham slice.
1-2 servings.
Total cooking time:
4 1/2-6 minutes.

title: karats kinderhook
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Mix tomato soup, sugar, mustard, pepper, vinegar and oil. Bring to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Set aside.

title: ratatouille
directions: Cook onions slightly, using little oil.
Add eggplant, pepper and celery.
Cook, stirring frequently, to keep from sticking. Add tomato or vegetable juice; simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes. Add zucchini; cook for another 10 minutes or so.

title: oven browned potatoes
directions: Place oleo and potatoes in skillet; cook about 4 to 6 minutes, stirring, until barely browned.
Line baking pan with foil, shiny side out.
Pour browned potatoes and oleo in foiled pan; salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn and put into large container or bowl.
In medium saucepan, mix the brown sugar, margarine and light corn syrup. Bring to a rolling boil.
Continue cooking for 1 more minute. This is called the soft ball stage.
To test, take off heat. After 1 minute, put small amount of mixture into a cup that is filled with cold water.
If you can form it into a ball, it is ready.
Remove from heat and add, quickly, the soda, salt, cream of tartar and the vanilla.
Mix quickly and pour over the popped corn.
Stir well to coat each kernel.
Place in flat pans and bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring occasionally.
This keeps well 2 to 3 weeks of stored in tightly covered container after cooling.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first four ingredients in a dish about 9 x 13-inches. Mix the mayo and sugar together and spread over the veggies. Sprinkle with shredded cheese and bacon bits on top.

title: crab dip
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems to equal 1/4 cup; place in small bowl.
Stir in crabmeat, bread crumbs, garlic, parsley, lemon juice, hot pepper sauce, minced onion and thyme. Spoon stuffing into each cap.
Line large, round plate with paper towel.
Place caps on plate in circular fashion, leaving center open.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Melt together milk, salt, butter and cheese.
Add bread crumbs, turkey, noodles, egg and onion.
Mix all together.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares to serve. Serve with cream of chicken soup diluted with 1/2 can of milk.

title: cream cheese cutouts
directions: In a large mixer bowl combine butter and cream cheese.
Let stand at room temperature about 30 minutes or until softened. Stir together flour and baking powder.
Beat together softened butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and almond extract and beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Divide in half.
Cover and chill about 1 1/2 hours or until easy to handle.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Remove and cool.
Pipe or spread Almond Frosting onto cookies.
Makes about 90.

title: potpourri
directions: Mix well and place in glass jar in your kitchen.
A teaspoon or two in a pan of water on back burner (simmering water) gives a delightful fragrance.
You can substitute grapefruit, lemon or lime peel.
Bay leaves can be crushed into mixture.
A vegetable peeler works well to remove peel from the fruit.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients.
Top with pecans.
Brown lightly in 350° oven.

title: baked potato topping
directions: Cream all together and serve at room temperature.
Spoon onto the hot baked potatoes.
Store leftover topping in refrigerator. Is also a delicious topping on broccoli, green beans or asparagus.

title: eve's crock-pot beans
directions: Add all together and cook on slow even overnight, if desired. Oh, so yummy and one dish you do not have to worry about.
Stir once in awhile.

title: marinated chicken
directions: In a measuring cup, mix salad dressing and soy sauce.
Pour 3/4 cup in large resealable plastic bag, and add chicken.
Seal the bag and turn to coat.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight turning several times.
Refrigerate remaining marinade for basting.
Drain chicken skin side up, on a rack in a roasting pan, Sprinkle with onion salt and garlic salt.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 45-60 minutes until juices run clear, brushing occasionally with marinade.

title: zucchini and squash slaw
directions: Twenty minutes before serving, cut each zucchini and yellow squash crosswise in half. Cut each half lengthwise into matchstick thin strips. Cut each radish lengthwise in half.
In a large bowl, with wire whisk or fork, mix olive oil, vinegar, mustard, dill, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add zucchini, yellow squash and radishes. Toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate, if not serving right away.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grape-nuts pie
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts in warm water for 10 minutes.
Mix rest of ingredients together, then add to cereal mixture.
Place in pastry shell, then bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 25 to 35 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer until well blended.
Enjoy!

title: tiger bites
directions: Melt marshmallows in 4-quart boiler.
Stir in peanut butter until all is smooth, then add the frosted flakes.
Press the mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Yields 32 bars.

title: sunset dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in a 9-inch microwave-safe pie plate. Top with soup and salsa. Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until hot. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oriental salad
directions: Drain off all liquid; rinse in water.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt. Add eggs, butter, milk and vanilla. Mix thoroughly with an electric mixer. Pour into unbaked pastry shell and bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour ingredients together and simmer over stove.

title: cheesy chicken mushroom
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken in pan.
Dot with butter, cover with foil and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
While chicken bakes, saute sliced mushrooms, sliced green onions, 2 tablespoons butter, 2 to 3 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce and 1 1/2 teaspoons garlic salt.
Spoon sauteed mixture over cooked chicken.
Top with Provolone cheese and bake again for 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve it up and enjoy!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken into baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers over mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: chicken cheese meltaway casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain and rinse. Melt butter in saucepan. Add onion and cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in flour, salt, thyme and pepper. Add milk gradually; cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Arrange half of the macaroni in the bottom of lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Put half the chicken over macaroni. Arrange cheese slices over chicken. Repeat layering once. Pour sauce over layered mixture. Mix crumbs and parsley. Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake in moderate 350° oven for 25 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except tomato sauce and form into a loaf.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or microwave on High for 12 minutes.
Drain and then pour over the tomato sauce.
Bake for 5 minutes or microwave for approximately 1 minute.
I usually make several loaves ahead and freeze in aluminum foil ready to take out for a quick meal.
Just thaw and bake.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
In a small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt and set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water heat to a boil, remove from the heat and stir 1/2 cup chocolate morsels and vanilla into saucepan.
Transfer to a large bowl add eggs one at a time beating on low speed.
Gradually add flour; blend and beat on medium speed.
Stir in nuts and rest of morsels, put into a greased 8 inch x 8 inch pan and bake 25 -30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: anytime fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed; toss lightly. Refrigerate.
Serve in salad bowl with lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries and mix with the sugar.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Dissolve the Jell-O in boiling water and cool. Mix all ingredients well and chill before serving.

title: mustard cheese cauliflower
directions: Clean cauliflower; cook whole in boiling water until done (tender).
Place in shallow pan.
Salt to taste.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard and spread on cauliflower.
Top with cheese and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: crusty beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add and heat mushroom sauce, salt and seasoned salt.
Cook noodles.
Grate cheese.
Arrange 1/2 noodles in large casserole.
Pour 1/2 the sauce over the noodles; top with 1/2 the cheese and repeat.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top should be brown and bubbly.
Makes very large casserole; can be divided in 1/2 and frozen.
Bake frozen one covered with foil.

title: 20 minute cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pie crust.
Blend in 2 1/2 cups sour cream.
Pour into crust and bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until set.
Filling will be soft.
Chill for at least 4 hours before serving.
Serves 20 to 16.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Cream butter gradually adding sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter alternately with milk.
Put into buttered shallow square cake pan (8-inches). Cover with sliced peaches all over.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Makes 7 pints.

title: cow pies
directions: In a thick boiler, melt on very low heat the chocolate chips and margarine, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool before eating.

title: snickerdoodles(penna. dutch christmas cookies)
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Combine shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs and mix until light and fluffy on medium-low speed of electric mixer.
Blend in the flour mixture. Chill cookie mixture until easy to handle.
Roll small balls in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until brown in 400° oven, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone, if necessary, and save broth.
Place stuffing mix, chicken broth and soups in a large casserole dish.
Mix well.
Add chicken, making sure all meat is covered with stuffing mixture.
Dot with butter; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour, then remove and allow the top to brown slightly.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar well.
Add eggs and flour alternately. Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: salmon balls
directions: Crumble salmon.
Gradually stir in other ingredients.
Form 2-inch patties and fry in shallow grease until golden brown.
Turn and brown other side.

title: chicken flautas
directions: Combine chicken, picante sauce, onion and cumin; mix well. Heat 1/2-inch oil in skillet until hot.
Quickly fry each tortilla in oil to soften, about 2 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of chicken mixture and 1 tablespoon cheese down center of each tortilla.
Roll tightly; secure with wooden pick.
Place seam-side down on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes or until crisp.
Serve warm with guacamole. Makes 32 appetizers.

title: sizzling roasted potatoes
directions: Scrub or peel potatoes, cut into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Toss with olive oil, Season-All, garlic powder and pepper.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes, uncovered, until crusty.

title: cornmeal popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Scald cornmeal with milk and add oil and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add the eggs and beat well. Heat well
oiled
muffin
tins in the oven until very hot and quickly fill each cup 2/3 full with batter.
Bake immediately 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve at once.
Makes 12 popovers.

title: bob's mom's banana bread(sugar free)
directions: Beat together oil and Splenda.	Add eggs and bananas.
Sift together and add flour, soda, baking powder, and salt.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat and add milk, beating again.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: To make crust combine flour, salt, baking powder, shortening, sour cream and egg.
Stir 70 times; batter will be lumpy.
Spread thin on bottom of a lightly greased and floured 9-inch pie pan. Batter is spread thinly on bottom but thicker on the sides.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potatoes (in skin) until done.
Peel potatoes and mash with fork.
Mix in sugar and vanilla (knead out lumps).
Roll out like pie crust on sugar-powdered board.
Spread on thin layer of creamy peanut butter.
Roll up entire spread into log shape. Slice into 1/2-inch pieces.
Chill overnight in fridge and serve!

title: easy marshmallow four layer bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix, spread and water until blended.
Pat into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes.
Layer marshmallows, candies and peanuts over crust. Bake 2 to 3 minutes or until marshmallows begin to melt.
Cool. Cut into bars.
Makes 24.

title: bill's chicken dinner
directions: Layer dried beef and chicken breast (skinless).
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over and bake 3 hours at 325° (2 hours covered, 1 hour uncovered).
Serve over rice.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain; mix with all other ingredients. Bake in a baking dish for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; debone and skin.
Place chicken in long baking dish.
Mix soup and broth and pour mixture over chicken.
In saucepan melt margarine.
Add buttermilk, flour, salt and pepper (makes a batter).
Pour over chicken and bake at 425° until crust is golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cover chicken with water.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken. Reserve broth.
Bone and shred chicken.
Set aside.
Discard bones and skin.
Saute celery and onion.
Using a nonstick pan, spray with Pam until soft.
Add flour; cook, stirring, until golden brown.
Add reserved broth, salt and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in reserved chicken and half and half.

title: easy wonderful potato soup
directions: Cook veggies until tender in 3 cups of water with 1 tablespoon (2 cubes) chicken bouillon.
Melt butter; add flour.
Stir in milk.
Add cream mixture to pot of veggies in water.
Stir; add milk if too thick.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: mexican deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks.
Mash egg yolks in a small bowl.
Stir in mayo and next 4 ingredients, and blend well.
Spoon or pipe yolk mixture evenly into egg white halves.
Garnish, if desired.
Although these eggs are not too spicy, prepare a milder version by reducing the amount of minced jalapenos.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, corn syrup and milk; stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Then stir occasionally to prevent burning.

Cook until syrup forms a very soft ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat, add butter and cool to lukewarm (110°). Add vanilla and beat until frosting is creamy and of right consistency to spread.

title: tropical apple salad
directions: Combine apple, banana, celery, walnuts and coconut.
To prepare dressing, blend together mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Fold whipped cream into mayonnaise mixture; gently fold into apple mixture.
Chill.
Arrange romaine in bowl; spoon in salad.
Garnish with additional unpared apple slices, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut candy corn
directions: Melt sugar and Karo syrup until it starts to boil.
Add peanut butter.
Mix together.
Then add Cheerios.
Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: ham salad for a crowd
directions: Cut ham in chunks and grind moderately fine in batches in food processor.
Empty minced ham into large bowl as you go.
Blend remaining ingredients into ground ham adjusting seasoning to taste.
Makes enough filling for 5 dozen finger rolls.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add spices and egg and beat.
Dissolve soda in a little warm water and add to applesauce.
Combine the two mixtures; add the flour in which raisins have been dredged. Bake in loaf pan for about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
This freezes nicely.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread as directed and crumble bread and cooked bacon. Layer cornbread and vegetables with dressing and repeat.

title: tennessee jam cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in jam and eggs.
Add combined dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans. Fill and frost with Brown Sugar Frosting.

title: oatmeal scotchies pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 - 375. In small bowl, combine flour, soda, salt, and cinnamon; set aside. In large bowl, combine butter, sugars, eggs, and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy. Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in oats and chips. Spread into a greased 15x10x1 baking pan. Bake 20-25 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and sugar and bring to a boil, let cool.
Chop into small pieces celery, green pepper, onions, pimentos, shoe peg corn, French cut green beans.
Drain peas, corn, beans and pimento.
Mix all veggies and pour cooled dressing on. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix again and drain off liquid before serving.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Hard-boil the egg; allow to cool.
Chop eggs, pickles and celery.
Dice onion. Combine all ingredients with enough salad dressing to cover.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in 8 cups water and 1 tablespoon salt for about 12 minutes or until tender. Drain. Arrange alternate layers of macaroni and cheese in a buttered baking dish.
Combine milk, 1/4 teaspoon salt and eggs in a bowl.
Beat well.
Pour over macaroni mixture. Dot with margarine. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: pretzel cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk, vanilla, almond extract and egg. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough into 4 square parts.
Divide one part into 12 equal pieces (keep remaining dough refrigerated).
Sprinkle about 1 teaspoon of colored sugar on board.
Roll each piece of dough on sugared board into pencil like strips and twist into pretzel shape.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine Crisco, water and salt.
Work in flour with fork. Then work in more flour until you can roll out.
Pinch 1/2 and roll.
Then roll out the other half.
Makes 9-inch pie crust (top and bottom).

title: raspberry sorbet punch
directions: Combine cranberry-raspberry juice, raspberry ginger ale and pink lemonade in a large container, stirring well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Pour chilled mixture into a large punch bowl. Scoop sorbet into punch.
Stir gently.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Line dish (round or pie pan) with beans.
Spread avocado on top of beans.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco sauce together; spread over avocado.
Spread salsa sauce over mixture.
Sprinkle tomato, onion and then the cheese on top.
Serve with taco or corn chips.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes and sauce mix from the box into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat to boiling the tomatoes, water and oregano. Pour over potatoes.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bean-corn casserole
directions: Stir all
ingredients
together.
Put in greased baking dish. Top with oleo
mixed
with crumbs.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, all at once, and beat until mixed.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with the milk that has been mixed with lemon extract. Beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Separate the eggs, putting the egg whites into small mixing bowl. Put the yolks and remaining 5 ingredients into a large mixing bowl and mix until well blended. Beat the egg whites, then fold into the batter. Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan. Cook at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pear conserve
directions: Melt
tablespoons
butter,
margarine or salad oil in heavy skillet over low heat.
Add 1 cup shelled pecans and stir until hot.
Avoid overcooking because pecans darken after being removed from
the
fat.
Drain
on
absorbent paper.
Sprinkle lightly with salt while still warm.

title: rock candy
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and water.
Heat to boil.
Lower heat.
Boil until temperature of candy thermometer reaches 300°.
Remove from heat, add desired color and add 1 teaspoon (flavor of choice) of oil based flavoring.
Example:
peppermint.
Pour into a rope strip on buttered marble.
Cut in sections and twist while it is hot.
Cut into small pieces while still warm.
Roll in powdered sugar.
(I do this by shaking in a bag.)
Sift off excess powdered sugar.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, onion and pepper.
Form into ball or log.
Roll in chopped pecans; top with cherry.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: herbed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In food processor, combine roll mix and herbs.
Add water and butter.
Process until dough forms a soft ball.
Add flour; process until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Place dough in pan and let rise for 15 minutes. Bake for 30 minutes until loaf sounds hollow when lightly tapped.

title: working girl's casserole
directions: Cook and cream potatoes.
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Using a spoon, make hole in center about the size of a saucer. Meanwhile, brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Fill hole with hamburger and onion; cover top with grated cheese.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage scrambling until brown.
Remove to casserole dish.
Pour off all but 1 1/2 tablespoons of drippings.
Saute celery, pepper and onion in drippings until tender (not brown). Mix rice and chicken noodle mix with 4 1/2 cups water.
Boil 20 minutes.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Mix with sausage seasoning. Sprinkle almonds on top and bake 20 minutes on 325°.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Decorate with bacon bits just before serving.

title: sweet potato dish
directions: Combine sweet potatoes (mashed) with first 5 ingredients. Place in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients (except pineapple) for topping with fork until crumbled and sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle with crushed pineapple.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana pineapple punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into molds and freeze.
When ready to serve, set molds out to soften approximately 30 minutes before serving.
Place in bowl and add 3 quarts ginger ale.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add powdered jello and orange juice.
Cool. Add 7-Up.
Works great in a mold!

title: good for you scones
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the whole wheat flour, cereal, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in the margarine until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Beat together the egg and milk. Add to the flour mixture and stir until well combined.
Knead on a lightly floured surface for 3 to 4 minutes or until smooth.
Roll out the dough 1/2-inch thick and cut with a 2-inch biscuit or cookie cutter.
Place the scones in a heated, lightly greased (vegetable cooking spray) or Teflon-coated frying pan.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Turn and cook 10 minutes more.
Yield: 14 scones.

title: crab-stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes or until tender. When cool enough to handle, halve potatoes lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp into a bowl, leaving a thin shell.
Set shells aside.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Layer chicken, broccoli and cheese in pan. Combine soup, mayonnaise and milk.
Pour over mixture in pan. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 45 minutes. Serves 10.

title: country skillet hash
directions: Cook onion and garlic in butter over medium heat until tender. Add potatoes, tomatoes, pork, green pepper and thyme.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.

title: porterhouse cookies
directions: Sift three times together the flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream sugar, brown sugar, butter and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and eggs and mix well.
Add sour cream.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix in chips and nuts.
Using teaspoon, spoon on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until light brown.
Transfer from sheet to paper towels once out of oven to cool.

title: baked scallops(portuguese)
directions: Mix scallops, sour cream, salt and pepper together.
Crumble Ritz crackers and layer bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with these crumbs.
Pour scallop mixture over crumbs.
Melt butter and pour over top layer of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: no-knead bran bread
directions: Stir together flour, dry milk and salt.
Combine yeast, sugar, warm water and cereal in a large bowl of electric mixer.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, margarine and 1 cup of the flour mixture.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Gradually mix in remaining flour mixture by hand to form a stiff, sticky dough. Cover; let rise in warm place until double in volume, about 1 hour.
Stir down dough to original volume.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes, or until browned.
Remove from pan; brush with melted margarine and let cool.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Syrup:
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter.

title: perfect banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and bananas.
Add egg whites, sour cream, and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add soda, salt, baking powder, and flour. Mix just until moist.
Pour mixture into large nonstick bread pan. Bake at 350° for 45-55 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 7 ingredients together and add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Divide dough in half and refrigerate in airtight container at least 2 hours.
Roll thin on lightly floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Decorate and bake at 350° for about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in 3 to 4 quart saucepan over low heat.
Cool. Add sugar, molasses and eggs.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Deep fry chicken wings in oil for about 12 minutes and drain. Mix hot sauces, butter, Cajun seasoning, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.

title: freezer biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and water; set aside.
Mix flour, soda, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk; mix.
Roll out on flour covered surface. Cut and place on cookie sheet.
Let rise for awhile and freeze until hard.
Put in closed container or freezer bag.
To bake, place frozen biscuits on greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Slowly add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Fold in carrots.
Bake in three layers at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: cream of potato puff
directions: Use 5 to 6 potatoes and make in usual fashion.
Combine cream cheese and potatoes, mixing well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato and bean casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix hamburger, salt and pepper.
In a casserole dish, layer as follows: potatoes, onion, hamburger, beans and tomato soup.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Add chicken soup to noodles.
Mix well.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Pour off fat.
Add tomato soup to meat.
In a casserole, first layer noodles with soup mixture, then put a layer of hamburger mixture and then some cheese over that.
Then repeat noodles, hamburger mixture with cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease pie plate. Beat all ingredients until smooth; 30 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater. Pour into pie plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with fresh fruit or Cool Whip. Or just eat it alone. Either way, it's delicious.

title: frozen holiday cukes
directions: Slice cucumbers thin and peel.
Slice onion thin.
Mix cukes and onion together.
Sprinkle with salt and let sit for 2 hours. Don't drain, then sprinkle sugar and vinegar over cukes.
Stir well; let stand 15 minutes and freeze.

title: texas casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook beef over medium heat, breaking into clumps with spoon when browned. Drain off drippings. Stir garlic, sugar, salt, pepper and tomato sauce into meat. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Butter the bottom of a 10-inch (glass) pie pan.
Spread with coconut. Place all other ingredients in blender container.
Blend well on high speed.
Carefully pour over coconut.
Be sure coconut is moistened.
Bake in oven at 350° approximately 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned and firm.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Surprise!
It forms its own crust.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar and salad oil together; heat until sugar is melted.
Cool.
Mix other ingredients; pour liquid over vegetable mixture.
Marinate overnight.

title: melt away cookies(also diabetic)
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and cornstarch.
Add flour until well blended.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Make 1-inch balls and flatten with a floured fork slightly.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes, until firm and light golden around the bottom.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and boiling water.
Add grapes, apples, orange and cranberries.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar, then add egg and beer all at once.
Don't knead it.
Put it into a greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan and bake it for 1 hour at 375°.
Serve immediately.
Can be prepared ahead and can be frozen.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add oil.
Mix buttermilk and eggs.
Store in refrigerator, covered.
Will keep 8 weeks in refrigerator. When filling muffin tins, just spoon into pans.
Do not stir. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Lightly grease muffin pans or spray with Pam.
Makes 48 muffins.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend for 1 minute on mix. Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until brown.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients.
Roll into balls in flour; brown in hot fat.
Place in casserole dish.
Add remaining flour to the fat.
Blend and add 1 1/2 cups tomato juice.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package directions until it's crisp.
As broccoli cooks, saute onions in butter.
After sauteing onions, add mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and garlic.
Heat on medium until cheese melts.
Set mixture of cheese aside.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: In glass bowl or on plate, layer in order listed.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour before serving.
Feeds 20 people.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Shape into patties. Peel the potatoes and slice.
Peel onion and slice.
Place a layer of patties, onion and potatoes in a greased casserole dish.
Put tomato soup over top.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust.
Line with sliced bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix together 1 can condensed milk and 1/3 cup lemon juice and spread over bananas.
Drain well 1 small can crushed pineapple and spread over mixture.
Prepare 2 packages Dream Whip as directed on package.
Fold in 3/4 cup chopped nuts and 1 small can coconut.
Pour this on top of pie.
Chill.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour and soda, set aside.
Mix butter, pudding, vanilla and sugars together; beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mix.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick chicken and noodles
directions: Heat cream of chicken soup, chicken broth and canned chicken to boil.
Add frozen noodles and simmer until tender, about 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 5.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Mix sugar, butter and peanut butter by hand.
Roll mixture into balls and flatten.
Mix chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler and heat.
Dip flattened balls in heated chocolate chip mixture and lay on waxed paper to cool.

title: *bread dough ornaments
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large, flat-bottomed bowl; mix well.
Add a little water a time, mixing as you pour to form balls of dough.
Knead 5 to 7 minutes, until smooth consistency.
Place dough in airtight container to prevent drying.
Use a little at a time, shaping and molding ornaments with hands.
Cookie cutters can be used.
Shape on cookie sheet covered with foil.
As pieces are added to make ornaments, moisten edges that will touch with water; if not, they will fall apart when baked.

title: bacon salad
directions: Make a salad with
all ingredients and garnish with egg slices.
Pour in Barbeque Dressing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix everything together and pour into casserole dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Cook and stir first 3 ingredients until sugar is dissolved and don't stir anymore.
Continue to cook until it reaches 300° according to candy thermometer.
A word of caution before stirring in cinnamon oil.
Turn on vent-a-hood and stir at arms length to prevent vapors from getting on arms and face.
Add food coloring and cinnamon oil.
Stir in well according to directions given. Pour into a greased pan and let set.
Break into small pieces.
Put in a covered bowl of powdered sugar and shake to cover pieces with powdered sugar.
Store in a covered container.

title: sekanice(czech easter meat loaf)
directions: Boil pork in salted water.
Forty-five minutes later, start to boil veal in another pan of salted water.
Let meat cool and take out bones.
Chop up meat; do not grind.
Add spices, crackers and 1/2 cup of stock; mix.
Add eggs, that were beaten separately (yolks and whites).
Grease pan (9 x 13-inch) with cold lard.
Bake until golden brown (1 1/2 hours) at 350°.

title: homemade brunswick stew
directions: Grind the meat and place in a large pan, along with broth. Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer a few hours, stirring frequently.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash apples and grind into small bits.
Cover with water and boil until soft.
Bring cider (or juice) to a boil.
Add apples, sugar and spices.
Cook 20 minutes more or until thick.
Can be put into a crock-pot to cook slow until thick.

title: curried honey dip
directions: In a small saucepan, combine honey and curry, stirring to blend well.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Transfer to a small bowl and let cool for 5 minutes.
Whisk mayonnaise into honey mixture until well blended.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate as long as 3 days.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in 1/2-inch slices; flour (use Ziploc bag).
Combine egg and milk.
Set aside.
Combine bread crumbs and seasonings.
Dip each slice into egg mixture and dredge in bread crumbs.

title: never fail pie crust(two crusts)
directions: Put sifted flour and salt into a bowl.
Make a paste with 1/3 cup of this flour and 1/4 cup water.
Cut 3/4 cup Crisco, plus 1 tablespoon butter into the dry flour until pieces are size of small peas.
Add flour paste to Crisco and flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly until dough comes together and can be shaped into a ball.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll out crusts about 1/8-inch thick.

title: orange slice bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut in pieces and roll in granulated sugar.
These freeze well.

title: apple puff
directions: In ovenproof skillet, saute apples, 2 tablespoons sugar and lemon rind in butter for 5 minutes.
In blender, blend eggs, milk, flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour the batter over the apples.

title: nebraska corn bread
directions: Mix soda with buttermilk until frothy.
Mix all ingredients together.
Lightly grease cupcake pans.
Fill each with batter. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with butter.

title: (diet) bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into muffin tin sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken with water and add margarine, onion, salt and pepper until chicken comes off bones. Drain chicken and cut into cubes.
Using broth, add enough water to make liquid totaling 6 cups.
Add potatoes and carrots. Boil 10 minutes.
Make pie crust. Layer the chicken and vegetables over the bottom crust.
Add the peas last.
Using 4 cups broth and 1 cup flour, stir with whisk until there are no lumps and cook until thickens.
Pour over vegetables in pie.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well 8 x 7 x 2-inch loaf pan. Combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and sugar in large bowl.
Add margarine with orange juice and egg, stirring into dry ingredients just to moisten.
Then add cranberries and nuts.
Bake one hour.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in eggs, 1 tablespoon sugar and the baking mix.
Beat vigorously. Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 20 times.
Roll dough into rectangle 16 x 9-inches.
Spread with butter and sprinkle with 1/3 cup brown sugar, raisins and cinnamon.

title: dobbs house luau black bottom pie
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Slowly add beaten eggs and blend well.
Mix together sugar and cornstarch and stir into egg mixture. Cook 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When custard coats the spoon, its done.

title: date bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; combine with date mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour in well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Use electric mixer.

title: baked spaghetti squash
directions: Cut the squash in half and remove seeds.
In baking dish, place cut side down and add water and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef with bell pepper, onion and salt.
Then add sauce.
Cook noodles as directed.
Put ground beef, then cheese and noodles in bread pan.
Repeat until full; on top should be ground beef and then cheese.
Bake in bread pan until done, about 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Stir lemon juice in berries. Toss with flour and sugar.
Pour into a pastry shell and bake until golden brown in a 350° oven.

title: jolene's berry delite
directions: In medium bowl, prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Spoon into an oblong ovenproof dish and chill until gelatin has set.
Top with cake slices.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge steak in flour; brown with onion in butter.
Add seasonings and water; cover and simmer gently until almost tender, 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Add soup and mushrooms; stir to mix.
Cook gently until beef is tender, about 30 minutes. At serving time, heat mixture piping hot.
Turn off and stir in sour cream.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Chill.
(Put chopped nuts, one cup on top and a cherry in the middle.) Serve with crackers.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Over low heat, heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti, chicken, pepper and parsley.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Cook time:
10 minutes.

title: pimento-pecan chicken salad
directions: "This is good served with wheat crackers."

title: snowballs
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add egg yolks, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites; add vanilla wafers.
Roll in 10 to 12 inch balls; refrigerate overnight.
Cover each ball with Cool Whip just before serving; sprinkle with coconut, if desired.
I use an ice cream scoop to make balls.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend together shortening, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add to this mixture eggs.
Beat well.
Add oats, baking soda, vanilla, baking powder, salt, flour and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix soda and oatmeal together.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes or until lightly brown.
Do not overbake.

title: squash patties
directions: Cook squash until done; drain water.
Mash squash.
Put in onions, eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Make into patties.
May need flour on them.
Fry in oil until done.

title: jambalaya ii
directions: Place chicken and sausage in a large pot and cover with water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until chicken is opaque and falls from the bone, 45 minutes.
(I usually do this the night before and refrigerate to skim the fat.)
Remove chicken and sausage, reserving broth.
Shred chicken.
In a large pot over medium heat, cook bell pepper, onion and garlic until onion is translucent, adding reserved chicken broth if necessary.
Stir in tomatoes, chili powder, pepper sauce, cayenne, Worcestershire and bay leaves; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir the shredded chicken, sausage and tomato paste into the spiced vegetables. Continue to simmer until flavor is as spicy as you like, adding reserved liquid as needed to thin.
Stir in 1 cup reserved liquid with the rice.
Simmer 20 minutes, until rice is tender.
Serve or continue to simmer as desired.

title: beef goulash stew
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; cook until onion is tender.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, ketchup, celery flakes, parsley flakes, sugar and pepper.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add macaroni. Simmer for about 1 hour, checking after 30 minutes.
Do not let macaroni get mushy.

title: potato bake
directions: Put potatoes in pan.
Cut 1/4 pound margarine in chunks over potatoes. Mix soup and sour cream; spread over potatoes then spread onions and cheese.
Mix corn flakes and 1 stick butter. Put over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Heat oven to about 375 degrees.
Spray or grease round cake pan.
In bowl, mix flour, corn meal, sugar, salt and baking powder. Stir in egg, milk and vegetable oil.
Mix well.
Pour batter into cake pan.
Bake for about 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot with butter on top or just plain.

title: individual praline cheesecakes
directions: In a smaller mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until well combined.
Add eggs all at once.
Beat just until combined.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in sour cream.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook the pasta following instructions on the box.
Rinse in cold water and let it drain.
In a medium size bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, 1 package of Mozzarella grated cheese, eggs, parsley, salt, pepper and nutmeg and set aside.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Gradually mix all ingredients together, a little at a time. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: doo-dads
directions: Mix.
Let stand for several hours.
Keep in tight container.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook 1 hour. Add cream of celery soup.

title: french toast
directions: Beat egg, sugar, flour and milk.
Add salt.
Heat pan with a little oil.
Dip bread in egg mixture.
Brown on both sides.
Eat with jelly or syrup.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: In medium bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla; pour into crust.
Chill approximately 3 hours.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: palestinian fasting cake
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, water, shortening, dates or raisins, nutmeg, cinnamon and ground cloves.
Boil together for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Dissolve in cup the baking soda and salt in 2 teaspoons water.
Add the salt/soda to the fruit mixture.
Combine and gradually add flour and baking powder.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan and bake at 325°
for 50 minutes.

title: summer berry soup (cold)
directions: Slightly defrost the berries.
Chop to a coarse puree in food processor or blender.
Stir in fresh berries, sour cream and wine. Taste for sweetness and add sugar or Equal to taste.

title: salmon stew
directions: Drain juice from salmon into saucepan.
Add enough milk and water to make desired amount (quart, gallon, etc.).
Bring to a boil; salt and pepper to taste.
Add a little butter, if desired. Add flaked salmon.
Return to boiling point.
Add thickening just like Chicken Stew.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into bowl.
Slice bananas into pineapple juice.
Mix.
Put fruit cocktail and pineapple in mix.
Add pudding.
Mix and chill.

title: fettucine alfredo(from cooking light magazine)
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Cook 8 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream cheese; cook 2 minutes. Add 1 cup Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly, until it melts. Pour over hot cooked fettucine; toss well to coat.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, fresh parsley and pepper. Yield:
4 servings (1 cup each).

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar and spices together in bowl, add eggs and beat slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 1 hour or until a silver knife comes out clean when custard is tested.

title: beefy macaroni skillet
directions: In skillet cook beef and onion until beef is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
Add macaroni; reduce heat to low.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Top with additional cheese if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix pudding and syrup and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: snapper in garlic and red pepper sauce
directions: Flour fish on both sides.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
(Do not let the pan get too hot.)
Place the fish, skin side down, in the hot oil and let brown.
It may be advisable to turn your flame down a bit at this point.
Turn the fish over.
Add the onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Stir them together, being careful not to break fish.
Add the fish stock and cover.
Raise the flame and bring fish to a boil.
Lower to medium until fish is cooked, about 1 minute.
Remove fish from the pan and place on warm plate.
Add tomato paste, a little cayenne pepper (optional) to the pan.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Turn flame off and add parsley, thyme, lemon juice and salt.
Pour sauce over fish and serve immediately

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°).
Add peanuts and salt.
Cook to hard ball stage (290°).
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter and soda.
Stir lightly.
Pour evenly into well-greased shallow pan.
Cool partially by lifting around edge with knife.
When firm, turn.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: dinner chowder
directions: Place vegetables and water into a large pot.
Simmer until tender, about 15 minutes.
While vegetables are cooking, and in a separate pot, make roux and milk mixture, using margarine, flour, seasonings and milk.
Add Velveeta.
Combine everything, then add parsley and tomatoes.
Heat to desired temperature.
Adjust seasonings.
Even better the next day.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cover 3/4 cup raisins with water and cook until tender.
In other bowl, mix sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch.
Mix sour cream and 3 eggs (separate the whites for meringue) and add to sugar mixture.
Cook in microwave stirring every little bit until thick. Add oleo and vanilla.
Put in a 9-inch pie crust and top with meringue.
Bake until brown.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Pour chilled evaporated milk into medium size bowl and whip with an electric mixer until soft peaks form (about 1-2 minutes). Mix water, lemon juice, and gelatin in microwave bowl and heat on high 1 minute.
Stir to dissolve gelatin.
Mix whipped milk, sugar, food coloring, and gelation mixture until thoroughly blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with inverted plastic dome and chill until firmly set, at least 1 hour.
Garnish.

title: rosy apple sipper
directions: In a large pan combine water, brown sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove spices.
Add juices; heat thoroughly.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 18 (1 cup) servings.

title: crock-pot candy
directions: Melt almond bark in crock-pot.
Add peanut butter; stir until mixed well.
Add Cap'n Crunch, Rice Krispies and pecans.
Stir until mixed well.
Add marshmallows and spoon out cookies on waxed paper.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: In bacon drippings, add diced onion; brown onions.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: baked "stuffed" pork chops
directions: Purchase assorted size pork chops on sale.
Mix favorite prepared stuffing according to package.
Using small roasting pan, stand chops on end, placing largest on ends and smaller, thinner chops in center.
Place 1 or 2 tablespoons of stuffing between chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on thickness.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Put chopped chicken on bottom. Slice eggs on top of chicken.
Mix soup, broth and pepper.
Pour over chicken and eggs.
Mix milk, margarine and flour thoroughly. Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
When cake comes out of oven, punch holes in top with large fork.
Pour pineapple (with juice) over the cake.
Let cake cool.
Pour pudding (prepared according to directions) over the cake and pineapple.
Refrigerate cake overnight or morning of dinner.
Before serving, cover with Cool Whip.
Add coconut and pecans over Cool Whip.

title: eagle brand cherry cheese pie(6 servings)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust; chill 3 hours, or until set.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ole timey scotch aigs(eggs)
directions: Hard boil aigs (eggs).
Shell.
Mix sausage, sage, raw aig (egg), peppah 'n salt.
Divide into 5 or 6 portions.
Wrap each portion around a hard boil aig, then roll in toasted braid crumbs. Deep fry in hot fat 'til a prutty golden brown.
Eat 'em cold.

title: sausage pasta soup
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
Brown sausage and onion in a Dutch oven.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomatoes, broth and water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add pasta; simmer 15 minutes more until pasta is tender. Serves 4.

title: honey-roasted fruit
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat
in	oil
over high heat in skillet, leaving meat in	coarse	chunks.
Add onion; reduce heat to medium and cook until
onion is tender, but not browned.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, corn
and
bouillon
and	bring
to a boil.
Stir in green pepper and boil again.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat; cover and
let
stand
minutes.	Fluff
with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: animal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.

title: sombrero spread
directions: Cook meat and minced medium onion over medium heat, stirring with a fork until brown.
Add taco mix and jalapeno relish. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Fry in enough oil to partially cover them.
Serve with syrup.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix pudding and milk, then mix in Cool Whip.
Break cookies in bite size pieces and stir into pudding.

title: easy french bread
directions: Mix as listed.
It makes a thick batter.
Let this rise until double in size.
Put on floured board; knead lightly (just enough to handle).
Divide into 2 loaves.
Bake in 8-inch round bowls for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Butter top when baked.

title: gluehwein(german mulled wine)
directions: Mix tea, spices and rock candy.
Boil for about 5 minutes. Let cool for a couple minutes.
Add wine and fruit slices. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute frozen broccoli and mushrooms in margarine until thawed. Mix in with soup and rice.
Grate cheese and mix in.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Blend all ingredients except coconut for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put 4 cups milk, 1 cup water and rice in heavy pan on high heat; do not stir!
Just before it is ready to boil, add 1/2 cup rice and stir.
(Do not let come to boil before adding rice; will not thicken if it does.)
Let boil on medium heat until rice is cooked, about 20 minutes.
Beat altogether eggs, vanilla and milk. Stir into rice mixture and bring to boil.
Cook for about a minute.
Pour into Pyrex dish and top with cinnamon.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli. Drain and combine with rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Blend shortening and salt.
Add molasses and egg and blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Fill small bowl with sugar.
Take some mix (walnut size) and roll in a ball in your palms.
Roll in sugar.
Sprinkle sugar on cookie sheet in place of greasing sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes. They won't look quite done after 11 minutes, but take them out and cool on sheet for a few minutes, then transfer to cooking rack. They'll finish baking while cooling.

title: potato puff
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan bring 2 cups water to boil; add potatoes; return to boil.
Cover and cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Using food mill or ricer, force potatoes into the clean dry 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in butter until melted. In small bowl, beat together eggs, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually stir into potatoes; add scallions.

title: dream cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat well after each egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in tube pan for 60 to 65 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies(no bake)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter or margarine.
Bring to a boil over medium flame and boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and cracker crumbs.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
When cool, the cookies are ready to eat.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute ham and onion in butter or margarine until onions are transparent.
Salt and pepper to taste. While ham and onion are cooking, whisk the eggs in a mixing bowl. When the eggs are well beaten, gradually whisk in the whipping cream.
Stir in ham mixture and Cheddar cheese.
Pour into prepared crust and bake until golden brown and the center is set, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
In a large bowl mix sugar, eggs, oil, vanilla, water and pumpkin until combined. Add flour mixture, 1/3 at a time.
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased loaf pans. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Let set for 10 minutes. Loosen with knife around sides and turn out of pan.
Lay on side of wire rack for 15 minutes or until warm.
Put in bread sacks, not foil, wax paper or Saran Wrap.
Store in freezer until needed.

title: easy lemon salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool until just beginning to set. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
A beautiful salad when placed in glass bowl and garnished with fresh kiwi fruit.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and cream until mixture becomes smooth.
Blend in milk.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.

title: chapli kabob
directions: Mix onions, green chilies, coriander leaves, flour, egg, chili powder, salt, ginger and garlic to the ground beef.
Mix well, adding 1 tablespoon of cooking oil.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz and thawed broccoli.
Add rice and sauteed mixture.
Turn into a large, covered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin mincemeat bread
directions: Mix first 6 dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Oil 3 loaf pans or use mini muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. These freeze well.

title: oven baked apple pancakes with sausage
directions: Brown sausages.
Combine remaining ingredients, except apple. Mix until batter is smooth.
Add apple.
Pour into greased 10 x 6-inch pan.
Arrange sausage on top.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in small amount of oil.
Place in single layer in baking dish.
Layer potatoes and onions over chops.
Season to taste.
Mix soup with 1/2 can water or milk.
Pour over casserole. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: pumpkin bread(low cholesterol)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in mixing bowl, make deep well in center. Add remaining ingredients and mix just enough to moisten all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool on rack. Wrap and store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 16 servings.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and margarine.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread on softened sausage.
Roll up. Put in freezer until firm but not frozen.
Slice and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: dill pickle roll-ups
directions: Dry off pickle.
Spread cream cheese on meat.
Place pickle on meat and roll up.
Slice to desired thickness.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add dry ingredients, then add milk.
Put in ungreased cake pan and top with peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
You can use any other kind of fruit.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter; saute vegetables 5 minutes over low fire.
Blend in flour, then chicken stock.
Let boil.
Season and let simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add cream.
Serve.

title: spanish rice with candules (pigeon peas)
directions: Put 3 cups of water in a pot.
Add candules, olive oil, olives, adobo, sazon and sofrito.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice, while stirring constantly.
Put on low heat.
Cover pot and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
After about 6 minutes, stir.
Cover and let cook for remainder of time.
Serve with your favorite meat recipe.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together the two cans of Veg-All, onion, and water chestnuts.
Add Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise.
Put into a greased casserole dish and top with herb stuffing mix.
Melt margarine and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix well.
Add more sugar to taste and chill.

title: cajun style linguine and chicken
directions: Stir-fry the first four ingredients.
Cook noodles as usual; drain and add a little oil and Cajun seasoning to noodles.
Add Cajun seasoning to the other stir-fried ingredients, then add them to noodles.
(Either top each serving, or combine it all together.)

title: 5 flavor cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken-etti(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Braise pimento, green pepper, onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper in butter until tender-crisp.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add chicken, vegetables, soup, mushrooms and chestnuts.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until bubbly.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini relish(makes 8 pints)
directions: Combine the zucchini, onion and salt and let set overnight.

title: cashew beef
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown beef and onion; drain excess fat.
Add soups, milk, green pepper, celery, mushrooms, cashews and cooked noodles.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stained glass dessert
directions: Cook pudding with one cup of juice.
Cool.
Add fruit; chill and before serving, add bananas.

title: cantonese eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant into strips.
Fry in peanut oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix pork and beans, pepper, onion and barbecue sauce together in a crock-pot.
Cook on high 30 minutes.
Mix in barbecue and cook on low heat about 3 hours.
Serve over fried cornbread.

title: baked corn
directions: Drain tomatoes and mix all ingredients in saucepan except cheese.
Cook over low heat; stir constantly, mixing well.
Pour into greased dish or pan.
Add grated cheese on top and bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot artichoke and tarragon dip(makes 2 cups)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in medium bowl. Transfer mixture to 3-cup ovenproof souffle dish or small casserole.
Bake dip until heated through, about 30 minutes.

title: ginger-peanut dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor and puree until smooth. Add water to thin, if necessary.
Transfer to a bowl. Serve peanut dip with fresh vegetables.
Yields 2 cups.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well; chill for 2 or more hours and serve.
Pour into center of rye loaf.
Surround outside of loaf with torn up pieces from center of loaf or serve in container surrounded with fresh vegetables.

title: golden fry batter
directions: Blend oil and flour.
Add egg and milk.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Dry food thoroughly, then coat generously with unseasoned flour.
Dip into batter, letting excess drip off.
Fry at 375° in oil 3 or 4 inches deep until golden brown.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Layer all ingredients in order in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, saute onion, celery and garlic in oleo until tender.
Add potatoes, carrot, peas and chicken broth.
If broth doesn't cover potatoes, add a little water.
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 30 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender. Do not drain; add milk, cheese and crumbled bacon.
Stir occasionally until cheese is melted.
Serve with sandwiches or hot bread.
Serves 6 polite people or 3 gluttons.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix juices in a large kettle.
Place in a punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and ice.
Don't put ice in the bowl first, you are apt to break it when you pour in the juice.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Break up pecans.
Stir all ingredients together and pour into a square greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sweet potato cake frosting
directions: Cream together cheese and butter.
Add vanilla and stir in confectioners sugar, then add nuts.
Frost cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mandarin orange pies
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice using mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip. Stir in orange pieces and pineapple.
Pour into 2 prepared pie shells.
(Butter crusts or graham cracker crusts are best.)
Chill and enjoy.

title: sausage and vegetable soup
directions: Pour soup and 2 cans of water into a 3 to 4-quart pot. Add onion, cabbage (sliced) or chopped kielbasa, caraway seeds and vinegar. Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes until vegetables are done. Makes 6 servings.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Bake in a 325° oven about 40 minutes. I bake in long cake pan.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours.
Roll in ball size of walnut, or use melon scoop to form.
Roll in cinnamon sugar.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 400°.
If too cool, cookies will spread too far.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: jean's shrimp salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Add all other ingredients, seasoning with salt, pepper and celery salt, and chill.
Sprinkle paprika on top for color.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
While cake is hot, poke holes about an inch apart with fork.
Mix together milks and pour over hot cake.
Pour pineapple and juice on top. Place in refrigerator.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Beat eggs; add all other ingredients to noodles and put in greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. If not serving immediately, turn temperature down to warm and cover with aluminum foil.
Serves 12.
This makes a good accompaniment to roasted meats or to a brunch buffet.

title: one-half gallon barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil for 5 minutes before using.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken, cheese, soup and milk.
Sprinkle with stuffing; drizzle with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add bananas; beat well.
Combine milk and vinegar; add to mixture.
Stir in salt, baking powder, baking soda and vanilla; add flour 1 cup at a time and last stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 1 large loaf of bread.

title: pecan squares
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Add broken pecan meats, sifted flour, baking powder and melted butter.
Add vanilla last.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: pecan roll
directions: Reserve 3/4 cup crumbs for later; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix remaining crumbs, pecans and coconut.
Melt margarine, milk and marshmallow cream in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Pour this mixture over first and mix well.
Spread reserved crumbs onto plastic wrap.
Wet hands in cold water; shape a handful of pecan mixture into roll; roll in crumbs.
Transfer rolls to clean plastic wrap, seal and refrigerate.

title: baked french toast
directions: Break bread into small pieces and put into a greased baking dish.
Mix eggs and half and half; pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or several hours before baking.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Dip chicken breasts in beaten egg and Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Saute in margarine.
Place in a casserole dish.
Saute mushrooms in same pan and add to chicken.
Pour chicken broth over chicken.
Layer Muenster cheese on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: feta sun-dried tomato bread crumbs
directions: Slice bread and let it set out overnight.
Mix cream cheese and feta.
Spread over bread slices.
Chop tomatoes very fine. Spread on top of cheese covered bread.
Top each bread slice with 1/2 Calamata olive.
Makes a great presentation on a tray.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Coat tomato slices with cornmeal. Season with salt and pepper. Saute in bacon drippings in a heavy skillet over medium heat. This cooks in about 10 or 15 minutes, turning over once. Okra is also delicious cooked this way. Cut okra crosswise and tumble in bowl with cornmeal.

title: apple drop biscuits
directions: Shred the apple into bits.
Mix together Bisquick, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour the apple juice into a bowl and add Bisquick mixture and shredded apples.
Stir until wet.
Batter will be lumpy.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, Crisco and eggs until creamy and smooth.
Add pineapple and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix. Add nuts.
Chill a few minutes which makes batter easier to drop from spoon.
Bake in 350°
oven.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Drain; arrange stalks in greased baking dish. Place chicken on top. Combine remaining ingredients, except butter and bread crumbs. Pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese. Combine butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna teasers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine in mixing bowl the flour, baking powder, onion salt and dash of pepper.
Cut in margarine until mixture is the size of small peas.
Add milk all at once.
Stir until well blended.
Add tuna and cheese and blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: german pot roast
directions: In hot oil in 5-quart Dutch oven, brown beef, turning on all sides.
Add carrots, onions, thyme, water, vinegar, juniper berries and salt.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 2 hours. Drain sauerkraut and add to Dutch oven, then cook an additional 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Take last 4 ingredients and mix together; pour over first mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: cold soup
directions: Mix soup, vegetables, water, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce to taste.
Let set overnight so flavors can blend.
Add salt to taste.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Start with eggs and sugar in blender; mix.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Mix.
Bake in 10-inch greased pie plate for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda. Add water, salad dressing and vanilla. Mix together all ingredients until well blended. Pour into greased and floured cake pans. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini delight
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, garlic, parsley, grated cheese and onions; blend.
Add Bisquick and zucchini; mix.
Pour into square greased casserole.
Bake on 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: baked beans for 50 people
directions: Mix ingredients to beans; place in pan and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: fast onions and tomato soup
directions: Place
onions
in
hot oil about 10 minutes, keep stirring. Add basil leaves, pepper and salt to taste.
Add 2 cups plum tomatoes after onions are limped.
Add water and bring to a
boil. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and add 2 beaten eggs last.
Pour them slowly; when cooked, serve hot.

title: saronno summer trifle
directions: In a saucepan mix cornstarch, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add butter or margarine and stir over medium heat until custard thickens.
Remove from heat and cool, covered.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Mix all but fruit topping in a bowl.
Scoop mixture into pie pan.
Pour fruit topping on top.
Refrigerate.
Don't bake.

title: fruit dessert or salad
directions: Mix pudding with liquid drained from fruit.
Use low speed on mixer.
When this mixture gets thick, fold in the fruits.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix
corn
meal,
flour
and sugar together thoroughly. Beat the
eggs,	then
add all ingredients and mix.
Pour into unbaked pie
shell.
Bake
at 300° for 45 minutes to one hour, until set. Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with condensed milk until it is thick.
Fold in Cool Whip, then strawberries.
Pour in 9-inch baked pie shell. Children love this pie.

title: fickle pickle franks
directions: Mix dressing, pickle and mustard.
Add hot dogs.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on rolls.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients of box mix.
Pour in oblong greased and floured baking pan.
Bake as directed on box.
Let cool.
Leave in pan.

title: butterscotch krunches
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot water in double boiler. Add broken chow mein noodles and chopped peanuts.
Stir until all well coated with butterscotch.
Drop by the teaspoon on wax paper then chill.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook on medium heat.
Combine sugar, milk and butter; cook until soft ball stage (235°).
Add pecans, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat and pour into 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion and celery in butter.
Add flour and pepper.
Toss to coat for 1 minute.
Slowly stir in chicken broth mixture, stirring constantly, until thickened and just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
In blender, puree up a little at a time until smooth.
Add milk and heat thoroughly.
Add cheese and heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted and soup is piping hot.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: t.t.'s party punch
directions: Mix punch and 7-Up in punch bowl and float sherbet.

title: cold oven popovers
directions: Break eggs into a bowl.
Add a cup of milk, flour and salt. Mix well.
Disregard small lumps.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Put in oven.
Set control at 450°
in very hot oven. Turn on heat and bake 30 minutes without opening the oven door. Then open door and remove.
Really delicious and easy!!

title: aunt effie's salad and dressing
directions: Tear lettuce and place in a large serving bowl.
Tear spinach in small pieces.
Place spinach in bowl and add all other ingredients; toss well.
Pour salad dressing over all and toss thoroughly.
This salad is better if made a couple of hours before serving and placed in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate bits in top of double boiler, over boiling
water.
Beat softened cheese in large mixer bowl until fluffy
and smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar, then eggs, one at
a time,
beating
after
each
addition.
Add
melted chocolate, cocoa
and
flavoring;
blend thoroughly.
Stir in sour cream
and pour
into chilled crust.
Bake at 290° for 1 hour and
30 minutes
(cake
will be slightly runny, but will become firm
as it
chills).
Cool
at room temperature, then chill at
least
5 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, top with
whipped cream, chopped pecans and 1/4 slice cherry, needed for decoration only.

title: coconut pineapple squares
directions: Mix 1/2 cup butter (margarine) and 1/4 cup sugar with fork. Add flour and mix well until crumbs form.
Then mix with hands into soft dough.
Press evenly into bottom of pan with 1/2-inch extending up sides.
Prick with fork.
Bake for 15 minutes. Remove from oven.
Spread pineapple evenly over crust.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to well-beaten egg.
Mix well.
Fold in melted butter and return to oven and bake 20 minutes.
Cool and cut.
Use 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 3 dozen.
For double recipe, use 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Remove the crescent rolls and unroll on a pizza pan (round) or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake according to directions on tube.
Cool. Spread the mixture of cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed and garlic salt over the crust.
Place a mixture of vegetables over the pizza; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cut round pizza into wedges or 9 x 13-inch into squares.
Makes about 12 pieces.

title: mexican fiesta salad
directions: Just
build
your own salad starting with the Fritos on down the
line.	Makes
a
good	light meal.
The ground meat sauce is just browned meat with taco seasoning in it.
Enjoy!

title: 8 layer mexican dip
directions: On a large platter, spread refried beans.
Next, spread frozen guacamole (thawed) on the layer of beans.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning; spread the flavored sour cream on the guacamole. Tomato and onion are spread on top.
Follow with cheese.
Finally, sprinkle olives on top of cheese.
Tortilla chips can decorate the sides of the dip.

title: chocolate truffle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease bottom of spring-form pan.
Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler.
Add flour, sugar and water; blend well.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry, and set aside.
