title: chicken stew in crock-pot
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high 4 to 5 hours or until carrots are done.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix and press with fork.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes (watch, depends on your stove).

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: Place sugar, Worcestershire sauce, sesame seed, poppy seed and paprika in blender.
With blender running, add the vegetable oil and vinegar in a slow and steady stream until thoroughly mixed and thickened.
Drizzle over washed spinach and berries or serve on the side.
Serve immediately.

title: country baked pork chops
directions: Layer onion in 4 sections in greased baking pan.
Add quartered apples on top, then the seasonings.
Place one chop on each section and cover chops with cider.
Combine cheese, butter and breadcrumbs.
Place mixture on top of each chop and pat down. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Beat round steak with salt, pepper and flour; saute in oleo with garlic and onion for about 45 minutes.
Add bouillon cubes, water, soups and mushrooms.
Simmer several hours.
Add sour cream just before serving over rice or noodles.

title: friendship pretzels
directions: Add yeast to warm water and sugar in large bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes for the yeast to grow, then add 1 teaspoon salt and flour. Knead in flour.
Roll out, cut and form into pretzels.
Bake on cookie sheets covered with foil.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt or poppy seeds.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Sprinkle pineapple in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Then add pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Sprinkle pecans next. Pour melted margarine over all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool, then top with Cool Whip.

title: mom's chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in electric frypan; add 2 cups milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, then add cornstarch that has been mixed with 1/4 cup milk.
Stir until medium thick consistency. Pour into precooked pie crust and chill.
Just before serving, put whipped cream on top.

title: my "sweet" cornbread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt, sugar, and egg together.
Add milk until texture is smooth.
Pour into "hot" black iron skillet with a little oil in bottom.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Good to serve with just butter and milk, or with your favorite soup!

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix together and pour in a dish.
Top with Duncan Hines yellow cake mix.
Melt 2 sticks butter and drizzle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Follow directions for Rich Egg Bread.
After kneading until smooth, divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll out one-half and spread dough with margarine.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and sprinkle on 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Add raisins or nuts.
Roll up longwise. Cut to desired size and place in slightly greased baking dish.
Do the same with second half of dough.
Allow to rise for a few minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Drizzle on powdered sugar glaze made of milk, sugar and a little vanilla.

title: beaufort stew
directions: Boil first three ingredients approximately 10 minutes.
Season to taste.
Add shrimp.
Boil shrimp to your preference of doneness. Let stand approximately 10 minutes.
Serves four.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water; drain.
Cook rice.
Combine with broccoli, cream of chicken soup, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Put stewed tomatoes in a blender.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Pour in cooking pan for 1 hour (slow heat).
Add your favorite toppings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix dry yeast and 1 cup warm water.
Set aside.
With mixer, mix Crisco, sugar and salt, then add the beaten eggs.
Stir in boiling water and the yeast mixture.
Add flour.
Knead for 8 minutes.
Put in greased bowl; let rise for 2 hours.
Roll out thin and cut in strips 2 or 3 inches long.
Dip each piece in melted butter and cross up in Bundt pan.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese tortilla wedges
directions: Generously sprinkle cheese on half of tortilla and fold bare half over sprinkled half.
Wrap in a paper towel and heat in the microwave about 15 to 20 seconds.
Remove and slice into pie shapes just right for young fingers to pick up and enjoy.

title: light chile verde soup
directions: Boil chicken; reserve broth.
Let cool; debone.
Combine stewed tomatoes and next 5 ingredients in a large Dutch oven. Bring to a boil over medium heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Add chicken to tomato mixture.
Stir in green chiles and remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: texas fruit tray
directions: Remove rind from cantaloupe and watermelon.
Seed cantaloupe and cut into 16 crescents.
Cut watermelon into 3-inch wedges and remove visible seeds.
Peel and cut into 1/2-inch cartwheels. Peel and section grapefruit.
Wash strawberries, blueberries and dewberries.
Arrange attractively on a large tray and garnish with mint leaves.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Cook pudding, jello, water and lemon juice until boiling. Pour into bowl.
Chill until thickened.
Blend in prepared Dream Whip.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until set (1 to 2 hours).
Garnish with additional topping and strawberries.

title: healthy salmon loaf
directions: Drain
salmon.	Reserve 2 tablespoons juice. Debone and skin salmon, if needed.	Mix all ingredients together including juice. Shape in loaf. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Add butter to flour like you do pie crust.
Add sugar.
Beat egg and add.
Form into loaf shape.
Let stand overnight.
Roll real thin.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Beat another egg.
Brush egg over top of dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place 2 peanut halves on each cookie.
Press into dough.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: hot cranberry and apple casserole
directions: Mix cranberries, apples and sugar in melted buttered pan.
Mix brown sugar, oatmeal and nuts.
Place on top of fruits.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt butter.
Mix butter, sugar, and spices together.
Roll apple and mixture onto crescent roll.
Bake until done.

title: carrot-pineapple nut cake
directions: Cake is very, very moist; a honey sauce similar to baklava syrup is poured over the cake while it is still warm.
Should be cut in small pieces as it is very rich and delicate.

title: walnut chicken
directions: Combine shoyu sauce, sugar, beer, ginger, garlic and chicken in a bowl.
Marinate for approximately 30 minutes.
Heat oil in wok or skillet and add chicken.
Stir-fry until chicken is cooked and soy mixture begins to coat chicken.
Add green onions, mushrooms and walnuts.
Cook 3 minutes, tossing mixture with slotted spoon.
Serves 4 portions.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter & sugar together.
Put into pie shell, keeping out 1 Tbsp. for top of pie to be used later.
Mix pudding and pour over peanut butter mixture.
Top with cool whip.
Then top with saved peanut butter mixture and garnish with nuts.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together the flour, brown sugar, chopped walnuts and melted margarine.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally with a fork.
Remove from oven and allow to cool.

title: dry orange salad
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Combine oil, onion, rice and other ingredients to skillet and cook until rice is golden.
Add water, soy, salt and paprika. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: cowboy pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Combine all ingredients, except salt and cayenne.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat.
Cook until tender.
Add salt and cayenne last 45 minutes of cooking.
Can be cooked in slow cooker for up to 48 hours.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed.
In a saucepan, combine pineapple with juice and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until thick and syrupy (about 20 minutes; stir occasionally). When cake is done, remove from oven and poke holes all over top with fork.
Pour on pineapple mixture and spread evenly over cake. Cool completely.

title: venison butterfly steaks
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a few splashes of Worcestershire sauce.
Place steaks in pan.
Slice onions and some mango on steaks, then cover with mushrooms.
Spread your favorite barbecue sauce over all.
Sprinkle Morton natural seasoning on top.

title: fettucini and brie
directions: Boil macaroni al dente (a little hard).
While boiling, soften Brie and mix until smooth.
Add oil and basil and mix.
Strain macaroni, place on serving platter and lavishly pour Brie mixture over top; toss.
Add cherry tomatoes sprinkled with grated cheese and pepper to taste.
Serve with salad and garlic sticks.
Delish!

title: kattie dids
directions: Mix caramels, milk and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons on greased wax paper.
Chill.
When hardened, drop in chocolate mixture and place on wax.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls (golambki)
directions: Saute onion in butter;	cut out and discard hard center core of cabbage.
Put cabbage
in
large pot of boiling water; boil until leaves are flexible
and can easily be removed from head (need
approximately
leaves).	Combine cooked rice, sirloin, pork
and
sauteed	onion.	Mix well and add salt and pepper
to taste.
Fill
each	leaf with prepared mixture and roll.
Place cabbage
rolls
with folded sides down in a deep electric skillet. Pour
2 cans of soup over rolls (do not add water).
Add raisins.
Cook
at	about 350° for about 2 hours until cabbage is tender.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, pour into casserole dish.
Melt butter and mix with crushed crackers. Put cracker mix on top of casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet turkey chili
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain skillet.
Put onion and garlic in skillet and cook until tender. Add turkey and chili powder. Cook 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Add tomatoes and bring to a boil. Stir in bacon and beans. Reduce heat and simmer 5 or more minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Clean and cut carrots.

Cook until tender, then cool. Boil sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, sauce, salt and pepper. Add carrots. Remove from heat and add tomato soup (undiluted) onion (diced), and green pepper (diced). Cover and put in refrigerator. Marinate about 2-3 hours.
Then re-heat and serve.

title: caramel-topped applesauce cake
directions: Place raisins in saucepan. Add enough water to cover raisins. Bring to boil. Remove from heat and let stand until cool. Drain off water.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Pour dressing over tomatoes, cucumbers, mushrooms and meat. Cover, marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight; drain. Combine sour cream, cheese and onions; toss with the noodles.
Top noodles with vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with additional cheese, if desired.
Garnish with tiny choppings of the green onion stems.

title: dairy potato bake
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together thawed potatoes, salt, pepper, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Top with cornflake crumbs. Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika for added color.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate shake
directions: Put yogurt, syrup and ice cubes in blender; mix.
Put on frappe speed; add rest of ice.
Blend until thick.
Add more ice for thickness.

title: jane's neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 1 stick butter and 2 of the eggs. Mix well and spread in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together with mixer 2 eggs, cream cheese, powdered sugar, pecans and vanilla. Gently spread over first mixture. Bake 35 minutes or until light tan at 350°.
Cut into squares. Serve with sprinkled, sifted powdered sugar or apricot jam or Cool Whip.

title: white trash
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine together.
In a large bowl, combine peanuts, raisins and Rice Chex cereal.
Pour the first mixture over the peanuts, raisins and Rice Chex.
Toss to coat well.
Then coat with confectioners sugar.
Store in jars.

title: morning greeting(servings:  4)
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in blender.
Blend until smooth.
May prepare ahead.
Freezes well.

title: cheese and peppers egg casserole
directions: Tear bread into chunks (should have 10 cups). In a greased, shallow 3-quart casserole or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, arrange bread chunks evenly. Sprinkle with Monterey Jack, Cheddar cheese and cream cheese. Top with drained chili peppers. In a large bowl, beat eggs until mixed. Stir in milk and spices. Pour over cheese mixture. Cover and chill for several hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: marinade for ribs
directions: If you have lots of beef, add water to sauce.
Boil meat for 35 minutes.
Marinate up to 24 hours.
Barbecue for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spray Pam on 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place thawed potatoes in pan. Mix 1/2 cup butter, soup, cheese, sour cream, salt and onion; pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle melted oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bo knows soup
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain.
Add in large pan the remaining ingredients. Simmer until hot.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix pudding and milk, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: heavenly chicken
directions: Combine chicken, onion, rice and celery in large bowl. Mix soup, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix mayonnaise and water and add to soup mixture.
Add mixture of soup and mayonnaise to chicken mixture in large bowl.
Place in shallow baking dish 9 x 13-inches.
Top with corn flakes combined with melted butter. Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves eight.

title: almond crunch
directions: Melt chocolate and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix until well coated. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: herb butter basted turkey breast
directions: Combine all ingredients, except turkey in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and set aside.
Place turkey breast, skin side up, in a lightly oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Baste with butter mixture.
Cover pan with foil.
Insert meat thermometer through foil into thickest portion of breast, making sure it does not touch bone.
Make an opening in foil so thermometer does not touch the foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until thermometer registers 170°, basting often with butter mixture.

title: mmmpossible taco pie
directions: Cook meat and onions until beef is browned. Drain. Stir in seasoning mix. Spoon into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs with wire whisk or hand beater until almost smooth. Pour over meat. Bake until crust is lightly brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake until cheese is melted. Cool 5 minutes. Cut into squares and garnish with lettuce, tomato, olives and sour cream, if desired.

title: cranberry-orange liqueur
directions: Put all ingredients in 3 to 4-cup glass jar.
Stir and shake to mix well.
Store, covered, in cool place 1 month.
Shake jar occasionally.
Strain through paper coffee filter.
Pour into bottles.
Makes 2 1/4
cups.

title: indian chicken
directions: Mix and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Cover and turn often.

title: happy thanksgiving blessing mix
directions: Mix together and package in little bags.

title: chicken wings(sweet and sour)
directions: Mix sauce and pour over wings.
Bake for 1
hour at 375°.

title: spanish style fried rice
directions: On medium heat, cook sausage in a large skillet until cooked, breaking it up fine.
Add rice, garlic, onion and spices, stirring constantly, allowing rice to get color from sausage and spices. Lower heat; add broth and water.
Add all other ingredients; cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Check to see if water has evaporated and add more water, if necessary.
Cook until rice is fluffy.
Mix before serving.

title: quick barbecue beef bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef and 1/2 cup of the onions in a 10-inch skillet until beef is browned; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Stir baking mix, milk and eggs until blended.
Pour over beef mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining onion. Bake 25 to 27 minutes or until crust is light golden brown. Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Cut up elephant into bite size pieces.
This takes about 2 months.
Cover and cook at 460° for 4 months.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with gravy.
This will feed 3,800 people.
If more are expected, add 2 rabbits.
Do this only
if necessary!
Most people do not like "hare" in their stew!

title: grilled chicken and mango salad
directions: Pour 1/2 cup of the dressing over chicken in shallow dish; cover. Refrigerate 15 minutes to marinate. Place chicken on greased grill over medium heat; cook 12 to 15 minutes. Slice chicken into 1/2-inch thick slices. Arrange greens in salad bowl; top with chicken mangoes, grapes and onions. Pour remaining dressing over salad. Makes 4 servings.

title: dirt pie
directions: Crush cookies in bag.
Layer cookies and Cool Whip.
Decorate top with flowers.

title: anita's herb toast
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on party rye, white and/or thinly sliced bagels.
Cut bread to desired size.
Bake 20 minutes at 300° until dry and toasty.
Store in bowl for up to 2 weeks (covered).
Prepare as needed or bake all at once and store in toast tins.
Excellent Christmas treats!

title: apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, spices, soda and salt. Add apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: grapefruit tzimmes(makes 6 servings.)
directions: Drain sweet potatoes; arrange in a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Top with prunes and grapefruit.
Combine juice, honey, salt and cinnamon or nutmeg.
Pour over potatoes and fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: poulet je ne suis pas or chicken i don't know
directions: You will also need one turkey bag in a roasting pan.

title: almond vegetable stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok.
Add almonds; stir until lightly toasted, about 5 minutes.
Cut beans into 1-inch pieces. Add beans, onions and mushrooms to almonds in skillet.
Saute until beans are just tender.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Pour into
a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: "souper" chuck roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place a large piece of heavy duty foil in a 9 x 11-inch baking pan.
Place roast in foil and sprinkle dry onion soup mix on roast.
Then, spoon both cans of cream soup onto dry onion soup mix.
Wrap foil around roast tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour per pound of meat.

title: mother's old fashioned cookies
directions: Mix to a soft dough.
(Place 1 quart flour in mixing bowl and work ingredients into center of flour.)

title: tangy salad
directions: Remove seeds from cucumber.
Mix all vegetables in bowl.
Mix in cocktail sauce.
Add a little parsley.
Let sit in refrigerator in tightly covered container overnight or at least a few hours to marinate.

title: one-pan turkey encore
directions: Arrange broccoli crosswise in a rectangular dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch).
Mix Bisquick, milk, egg and soup; beat 30 strokes with wire whisk.
Pour over broccoli in center of dish.
Sprinkle with turkey, cheese and pimentos.
Bake until center is almost set, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: okra, tomatoes and corn medley
directions: Cook okra, onion, garlic and parsley in oil.
Season and add corn and tomatoes.
Let simmer about 20 minutes.
May be placed in oven and reheated.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together Bisquick, milk and Cheddar cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.

title: czechoslovakian strawberry cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour and walnuts. Spoon half the batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread strawberry jam on top.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cut into squares.

title: parmesan twists(appetizer)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In pan, combine cheese and seasoning. Divide dough into 8 sections.
Divide each section into 4 pieces. Roll each piece into a 4-inch rope.
Dip each rope in butter.
Roll in cheese mix.
Twist rope 3 times.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake for 7 to 9 minutes or until golden brown.

title: head cabbage kim chee
directions: Shred cabbage.
Mix with crushed garlic.
Add remaining ingredients according to taste.
Let mixture sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips, chocolate bar and chopped nuts.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Place in greased pan or Corning Ware dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and put chips on top.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: curried beef and rice
directions: Brown chopped onion in oleo.
Add ground chuck, salt and pepper to taste.
Continue cooking until ground beef is browned. Drain all liquids.
Add rice, mushrooms and juice, curry powder, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, sour cream and bouillon cube dissolved in water.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°, or longer, if rice is not tender.
Add a little bouillon when re-warming.

title: baked corn
directions: Fry mango in shortening. Add milk, 1/2 cup corn liquid, seasonings and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts. Add slightly beaten egg yolks, bread cubes and corn. Beat egg whites stiff. Fold in.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm in center. Serves 8.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels with water, mix in pecans.
Drop onto greased wax paper (I use pam spray).
Let set about 1 hour or more.

title: turkey meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix all ingredients, except chili sauce.
Shape into about 20 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Bake until brown, 15 to 20 minutes, and drain.
Heat chili sauce until hot.
Serve with meatballs.
Serves 5 with 265 calories per serving.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: Mix thoroughly and sprinkle with awareness.
Bake in moderate oven of every day life, using as fuel all the grudges and past unpleasantness.
Cool.
Turn out on a platter of cheerfulness.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff in small mixer bowl.
Mix egg yolks, milk and oil and mix well in large mixer bowl.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour 1/2 cup in waffle iron and cook until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburger in pressure cooker just until it isn't pink. Add onion, garlic powder, chili powder, cumin seeds, tomatoes and about 1 cup water.
Bring up pressure and cook 20 minutes.
Cool. Then add beans.
Keep in refrigerator one day before putting in containers to freeze.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender container. Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use. Yield:
14 ounces.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pink dream
directions: Stir all together. Refrigerate. Add nuts if you like.

title: hot relish(canning!)
directions: Combine tomatoes, sweet peppers, salt and alum.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Add all ingredients.
Heat just to simmering point.
Remove from heat and can.
Yields 9 pints.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Fry bacon crisp, drain and put aside.
Fry chicken and onion in bacon grease until chicken is cooked.
Add soup, milk and garlic to chicken. Add the Mozzarella. Stir until blended. Add spaghetti. Stir until well blended.
Pour into dish and top with Parmesan cheese and crumbled bacon. Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes or until bubbly and thick.

title: nugget squares
directions: Beat eggs, oleo and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Add 1/2 of chocolate chips and some nuts.
Add 1/2 cup coconut. Spread dough in greased pan, then pat down dough and add rest of chips, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple fluff
directions: Combine orange jello and crushed pineapple; cool in refrigerator. When cool, remove and add buttermilk and Cool Whip. Stir and refrigerate.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Mix last 2 ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, pie filling and eggs together and beat well.
Spread half the batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle with half the cinnamon-sugar.
Repeat with remainder of batter and cinnamon-sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: suf-soof (mint and parsley salad)
directions: Soak wheat in water for 1 hour.
Drain; press out moisture. Mix with onion.
Add parsley, mint, tomato, lemon juice, olive oil, salt and pepper.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, oil and dry ingredients; add flavorings. Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
When done, cool slightly and then flip from pans.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and 10x sugar.
Mix instant chocolate pudding and 3 1/2 cups milk.
Mix Cool Whip into pudding mix and combine with first mixture. Crush Oreo cookies and keep separated.
In plastic flowerpot alternate with cookie mixture and pudding mixture, beginning and ending with cookies.
Decorate. Serve with shovel and put flower into last mixture.
It will look as if this is a flowerpot.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, jello, fruit, nuts, and Cool Whip.
Can be served now.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Dice chicken and cook in vegetable oil until done. Add taco seasoning and cook according to directions on the package. Tear tortillas into bite-size pieces and cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with them. They should overlap. Layer chicken, beans, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Sprinkle chopped onions and cover with cheese (as much as you like). Final layer should be black olives.

title: sourdough bread(you must already have starter.)
directions: Refrigerate and feed every 5 to 7 days with the listed ingredients.
Mix well and add to the Starter. Set out of refrigerator all day. Take out 1 cup to use when making bread. Return remainder to refrigerator (covered) and feed again in 5 to 7 days.
If not making bread after feeding, give away or throw away one cup.
Starter must be fed each 5 to 7 days.

title: pineapple fudge
directions: Bring to boil cream, sugar and butter. Add drained pineapple; cook to soft ball stage (238°), stirring to prevent burning. Cool to lukewarm and add lemon juice. Beat until smooth. Pour in buttered pan.

title: pretzel drops
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave on High until smooth.
Add crushed pretzels and stir to mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: fern's damson rounds
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Cut 4 rounds from each slice. Spread with cream cheese and top with a dollop of preserves. Great for last minute guests.
Can be varied by using red or green pepper jelly.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add to dry ingredients.
Stir well until smooth.
Start on high temperature, then reduce to medium heat.

title: hot monterey rice salad
directions: Cook ground beef with taco seasoning.
Add salt, lemon juice and pepper sauce to mayonnaise; mix well.
Stir into meat mixture. Add rice, celery, green pepper, onion and tomatoes; mix well. Turn into 3-quart casserole sprayed with vegetable spray.
Top with crushed corn chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, being careful not to burn.
Fill canning jars and process for 20 minutes.

title: easy cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in dish; melt cheese and oleo together and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle crumbs over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; put one potato in each bag.
Place all 4 potatoes in microwave on High power for 5 minutes.
Turn potatoes and cook on High power for 5 more minutes.
Your potatoes should be baked just right.

title: sno-ball cake
directions: Chill mixture in refrigerator until thick but not firm.
Whip 2 packages of Dream Whip with 1 cup milk, then add pineapple mixture to Dream Whip and blend.
Tear angel food cake into 1-inch pieces or smaller.
Line large mixing bowl with Saran Wrap, then put layer of cake, layer of pineapple mixture.
Repeat, adding layers (3 or 4 layers of each) ending with layer of mixture.
Chill until firm, then turn cake upside down.
Remove Saran Wrap and frost with 1 package of Dream Whip.
Cover with coconut.
Keep refrigerated until served.

title: stir-fry for 3
directions: Combine soy sauce, sugar, cornstarch and meat.
Set aside. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in heavy skillet. Stir-fry vegetables until they are just starting to soften on the outside.
Remove to a plate. Clean wok or skillet and heat 2 tablespoons oil. Add meat and stir-fry 4 to 8 minutes until brown. Return vegetables to pan and reheat, stirring constantly. Serve with rice.
Contains 350 calories.

title: white chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Add nuts and cereal. Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Let set at least 1 hour. Break up.
Store in cookie tin.

title: river city chili
directions: Brown meat; pour off excess grease.
Add all other ingredients.
Let boil for 15 minutes, then simmer for 2 hours with lid on.
Add water to thickness desired.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook the onion until limp in butter in a saucepan. Add bouillon, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer (do not boil) gently for 30 minutes.

Pour soup into 4 individual ovenware bowls. Cut toast into 1-inch squares and float on soup. Sprinkle all with cheese and if possible, bake in hot oven (475°) or slip under broiler to melt cheese just before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add vinegar and food coloring.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add vanilla and then add to mixture.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Bake cake in two or three greased and floured, round pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: microwave overnight tuna casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk in microwave-safe bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients except 1/4 cup cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cover and microwave on High 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese. Let stand 5 to 7 minutes until cheese melts.

title: icees
directions: You will also need 3-ounce size paper cups and popsicle sticks.

title: garden veggie quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
On floured surface, roll out dough to 14-inch round; fit into a 9 x 2-inch fluted quiche pan with removable bottom.
Bake dough for 20 minutes; let cool. Meanwhile, over medium heat in skillet coated with cooking spray, cook broccoli, squash, leek and red pepper for 8 minutes.
Whisk together next five ingredients.
Layer vegetables and Swiss cheese in crust; pour in egg mixture.
Bake 50 minutes or until top puffs.
Makes 10 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jeremy's crazy cake(excellent, moist, easy!)
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured rectangle baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Boil until a few drops placed in a cup of cold water forms a soft ball when rolled between the thumb and second finger (235° on a candy thermometer).
Then pour half the boiling mixture over the stiffly beaten egg whites and stir.
Return the remaining half of the mixture to the heat and boil until a few drops placed in a cup of cold water form a hard ball (260° on a candy thermometer).
Combine with egg mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla, working fast.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on a well buttered cookie sheet.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in skillet until beef is browned. Add flour, catsup and water to beef.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: ham and swiss dinner rolls
directions: Combine butter, mustard, worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and onion soup mix.
Simmer for 10-15 minutes.

Split dinner rolls and stack with ham and cheese, making small sandwiches. Place sandwiches in a 9 X 13 baking dish and pour soup mixture over all. Cover and refrigerate overnight.	Bake at 325 degrees for 20-30 minutes.

title: one-pot sausage jambalaya
directions: Fry sausage down; let brown and remove excess grease.
Add about 1 cup water, onion soup mix and any other seasonings you wish.
Let cook for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add rice and about 2 to 2 1/2 cups water.
Cook approximately 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Then in another pot, add a little butter, then add green onions and yellow onions in the jambalaya after it is cooked.

title: smothered steak
directions: Batter steak pieces in flour.
Brown quickly in hot oil. Place meat in slow cooker alternately with onion, pepper, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or cook on high for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple coconut cloud pie
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and flour.
Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir half the pineapple mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Combine with remaining hot mixture.
Cook a minute longer.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and lemon juice.
Cool.
Turn into baked pie shell.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Put blueberry pie filling on the bottom of your 9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex dish, then pour can of pineapple over it.
Dump cake mix (powder) over next.
Melt the butter or margarine and pour over, then add your nuts and coconut.
Bake at 325° for approximately 60 minutes.

title: bruschetta
directions: Slice and butter French bread. Brown/toast bread in oven. Slice tomatoes; drizzle olive oil over tomatoes. Mix in garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and Parmesan. Slice white cheese and lay slice on toasted French bread. Cover top of bread/cheese with tomato mixture. Return to oven and melt cheese. Serve warm if possible; works as an appetizer or main dish.

title: delicious chocolate banana cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites, applesauce, water and vanilla until blended.
Beat in 1/3 of yogurt.
Beat in 1/2 of flour mixture, blending well.
Beat in half of remaining yogurt.
Beat in rest of flour.
Beat in rest of yogurt.
Beat in banana until smooth.
Pour into sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked (or grilled) vidalia onions
directions: Peel onion.
Pare onion, leaving 1/4-inch on bottom of onion. Fill with bouillon cube and butter.
Wrap in foil, sealing tightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or grill for 30 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mash saturated bread to make paste.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Blend well.
Make into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls.
Put on deep cookie sheet with sides touching.
Bake at 350° until brown and cooked through.
Remove to paper towels or brown paper to drain and cool.
Store in closed container until ready to use. When ready to use, just heat in spaghetti sauce or moisten in oven.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until smooth and well blended.
Add chili sauce, lemon juice, onion juice and Worcestershire.
Mix.
Add shrimp that has been patted dry.
Mix. Refrigerate.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Mix milk, flour and sugar.
Pour on oleo, then add fruit.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits. Mix cinnamon and 2/3 cup sugar. Put into bag and shake a few pieces of biscuits at a time until well coated. Press into generously greased Bundt pan. Place margarine and 1 cup sugar in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Pour over biscuit pieces. Bake 30 minutes on 425°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip until mixed evenly.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Refrigerate.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Mix all together and simmer for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook in crock pot 6 to 8 hours on low heat.

title: potato salad
directions: Place potatoes and onion in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix lightly with French dressing.
Chill an hour or two. Toss lightly with salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Carefully blend in eggs.
Mix a little minced pimiento and parsley for color.
Add extra seasoning or dressing to taste.
Serve in bowl or on platter surrounded with salad greens, tomato sections, slices or wedges of hard-cooked eggs and cucumber sticks.
Garnish with paprika. Serves 6.

title: zippy cranberry cooler
directions: Combine chilled cranberry juice with frozen lemonade and cold water.
Add ice cubes and chilled Squirt just before serving. Yield:
1 gallon.

title: pickled okra
directions: Sterilize jars.
To each jar add 1 clove garlic, 1 dill seed, okra and hot peppers (if desired).
Boil together vinegar, water and salt; pour over and seal.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme in bowl; set aside. Bring to boil the sugar and water.
Boil 4 1/2 minutes (time closely).
Then pour over Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter. Whip and stir until all is mixed.
Add nuts.
Pour into large buttered pan.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Mix together with wire whisk.
Refrigerate after mixing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together 1 stick margarine and cornbread dressing.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, line bottom with 2/3 of stuffing mix.
Add squash mixture.
Put rest of dressing mixture on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix liquid ingredients separately, then combine together.
Handle as little as possible.
Drop into muffin tins lined with paper cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon together; stir into creamed mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with glaze while warm.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and let set.
In a bowl, combine soups, chilies, enchilada sauce and milk.
In a pan, put a layer of tortilla pieces, layer of hamburger, layer of soup mixture and a layer of cheese.
Then repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve with corn chips.

title: hot spiced orange juice
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pan.
Cook on medium high until slightly boiling, stirring occasionally.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes (or longer if desired).

title: pork and bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer the crushed pineapple.
Spoon in the cherry pie filling and spread.
Sprinkle the cake mix evenly over cherry pie filling. Take spoon; cut cake mix down into juice.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Spread chopped nuts over cake.
Layer ingredients in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add pureed bananas and mix until smooth.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, form a crust by mixing 1 stick of butter (melted) and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix together 2 sticks butter (softened), eggs, powdered sugar, vanilla and butter flavoring to form the filling.
Beat 10 minutes at high speed.
Spread filling over crust and chill.
Slice bananas lengthwise and put on filling. Cover with crushed pineapple and top with the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top and chill.

title: toffee treats
directions: Cream
margarine
and sugar well.
Add egg and vanilla. Add flour;
mix
well.	Spread	on
a greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.	Remove from oven.
Spread at
once with melted chocolate chips; sprinkle on nuts.
Cool. Cut into
18 portions.	Top
with a scoop of ice cream; spoon sauce over that. Serves 18.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Cook or steam and drain vegetables.
Lay in unbuttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Lay slices of cheese on top, then sprinkle crushed crackers over vegetables and cheese.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix with soup, cheese, Durkee sauce to taste and water chestnuts.
Season to taste; put cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Bake in 2-quart casserole.

title: vegetable and cheese enchiladas
directions: Saut pepper, onion, garlic, mushrooms and zucchini in olive oil over medium heat until onion is translucent.
Add beans, tomatoes, chili powder, cumin and coriander.
Remove from heat. Mix Ricotta and yogurt together in a small bowl.
Soften tortillas by steaming in the microwave for 20 seconds on High power.
On each tortilla, place three teaspoons grated cheese and two tablespoons yogurt mixture.
Roll tortilla around cheese mixture and place in baking dish, seam-side down.
Repeat with remaining tortillas.
Top tortillas with bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Use to brush on steak, roasts, spareribs, chicken and frankfurters during cooking.
Yield:
approximately 1 1/4 cups.
(Old recipe.)

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes.
Slice kielbasa and partially cook broccoli and grated cheese.
Alternate sliced kielbasa, broccoli and grated cheese to fill casserole dish 3/4 full.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put mashed potatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until warmed.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Combine first three ingredients in medium-sized pot.
Over medium-low heat, cook to light soft-crack stage (265°).
Add soda and butter.
Mix well.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: egg noodles
directions: Add flour to make stiff dough.
Roll thin and let dry.
Slice and unroll to cook.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil.
Add onions and saute for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve cubes.
Gradually add noodles and salt so liquid keeps boiling.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder. Cook 4 minutes more.
Add milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add pepper to taste.
Receipe may be cut in half.

title: butternut squash pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix ingredients and put in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients in medium size pan and simmer 10 minutes or until warm.
Makes 4 cups.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Place carrots and sliced chestnuts in a buttered casserole. Combine Cheez Whiz and soup together.
Pour over carrots and chestnuts.
Mix well and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well (flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda).
Add water, stirring quickly.
Add salad dressing and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased pan, one 10-inch or two 8-inch pans, at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on rack and frost.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into lightly greased pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, cocoa, water, flour, vanilla and well beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cut dough into 1 1/2 to 2-inch pieces, covering bottom of greased pan.
Add brown sugar and margarine (mixed).
Sprinkle pudding and 1/2 cup chopped nuts over top.
Cover in warm place to rest overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and butter to a boil; boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop quickly onto waxed paper by teaspoonfuls.
Let cool.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shells.
Chill. Makes 2 pies.

title: wanda's pipin' hot buffalo wings
directions: Wash wings and sprinkle with onion powder and salt.
Fill large frying pan halfway with oil and let oil heat up.
Fry chicken and drain.
While chicken is frying, heat hot sauce in saucepan.
Chop margarine in half and drop into sauce.
When margarine is completely melted, add cayenne and jalapeno pepper. Simmer on low heat until all chicken is fried.
Place chicken in a lasagna pan and pour sauce over chicken.
Your pipin' hot chicken wings are ready to serve!

title: english matrimonials
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and oats.
Work in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Press 1/2 of mixture evenly into bottom of a greased pan.
Spread with jam.
Press remaining mixture over jam, covering it completely.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Combine.
Cook to a soft ball.
Take off heat and beat.
Pour into a greased dish or pan.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream the margarine with the sugar. Add the cheese and flour. Cream all ingredients together.
Drain the apples and add to mixture. Grease bowl. Add mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Peel and freeze ripe bananas.
Just before serving, cut frozen bananas into 1/2-inch slices.
Place in a food processor or blender and blend, adding just enough milk to reach a thick consistency.
Do not add too much milk or you will make a milk shake.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: aunt doll's hot cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring well.
Pour into cup and top with a marshmallow.
Yields 8 cups.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water; drain.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg until thoroughly combined.
Spread mixture evenly in pan. Saute ground chuck, onion and green pepper in oil until meat is brown; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, oregano and garlic salt. Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Layer and top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese over top and bake an additional 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and just begins to brown.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: crushed sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine the sweet potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup melted butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased casserole.

title: quick and easy peach cake
directions: Sprinkle one box of cake mix over peaches.
Pour one stick of melted butter over mix.
Bake in ungreased pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Melt all ingredients together on low heat, stirring well. Grill chicken 45 to 50 minutes over medium heat.
Turn.
Grill on low and baste chicken for the last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: skillet pasta and vegetables
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
In 10-inch skillet, melt butter until sizzling.
Stir in garlic. Stir in remaining ingredients except pasta and cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisp tender (4 to 6 minutes).
Stir in pasta.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until heated through (2 to 3 minutes). Stir in cheese and serve immediately.

title: potato soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, saut onion in butter until tender.
Add dip, soup and milk.
Stir until soup is smooth.
Add boiled potatoes. Cook on medium heat until potatoes are done.
Can be topped with crumbled bacon, cheese, etc.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato and green bean casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Boil the potatoes until soft. Drain and mash. Chop the green beans. Mix together the potatoes, beans, garlic, oregano, ricotta, oil, and eggs. Place the mixture in a lightly greased 12 inch cake pan. Mix together the milk and breadcrumbs. Spread the crumbs over the mixture. Bake for 40 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve warm.

title: north carolina shrimp sauté
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add shrimp, mushrooms, green pepper and garlic. Saute until shrimp turn pink, about 3 to 5 minutes. Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions; drain and place on a large serving platter.
Top with shrimp
mixture. Sprinkle with cheese, salt, pepper and parsley. Toss well. Garnish with lemon. Serve immediately. Yield: 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole dish.
Add chicken.
Mix 1/2 can of soup and 1/2 cup chicken broth; pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix and rest of soup and broth together to moisten the stuffing.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serves 6.

title: almond joy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease cookie sheets. In a large bowl, cream together the butter, white sugar and brown sugar until smooth. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, then stir in the vanilla. Combine the flour, baking soda, and salt, stir into the creamed mixture until well blended. Finally, stir in the chocolate chips, coconut and almonds.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto the prepared cookie sheets.
Bake for 8-10 minutes in the preheated oven. Allow cookies to cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: zucchini flats
directions: Beat batter ingredients with wire whip, cover and refrigerate for at least 15 minutes.
Cut zucchini in half crosswise, then in lengthwise slices about 1/4 inch thick.
Dust lightly with flour. In large frying pan, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Dip zucchini slices in batter mixture to coat each side.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan, if desired, and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, onion and pimento.
Mix well.
(Add a small amount of milk if mixture is too stiff.)

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, gelatin mix, eggs and cooking oil until blended.
Stir in blackberries.
Bake in greased and floured layer cake pans at 350° until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; let cool.
Chop into medium chunks.
Mix all ingredients and add chicken.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or serve chilled.

title: banana split cake
directions: To make crust, use first 2 ingredients by melting oleo with crumbs.
Pat firmly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and oleo for 15 minutes with beater; pour into crust.
Slice bananas and arrange on top of mixture.
Top with pineapple and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries, cover and place in refrigerator, chilling overnight for best flavor.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak up into pieces; dip in flour and fry both sides. Put into a roaster sprayed with Pam.
Mix catsup and water.
Pour over steak; put onions on top and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cocoa chiffon cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a large bowl.
Make a "well" in mixture; add oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla (in order).
Beat until smooth.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In double boiler, melt chips and milk together.
Add walnuts and marshmallows; pour into buttered 9-inch square pan. Refrigerate at least 2 hours; cut into squares.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Cut chicken in small portions.
Sprinkle with salt and lime juice.
Set aside for 1 hour.

title: potato gnocchi
directions: Blend potatoes, eggs, flour and seasonings well together.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Drop into boiling water to cover and allow to simmer until they float to the surface; drain well.
Place in a greased casserole, alternating with layers of grated cheese. Top with bread crumbs.
Pour over melted butter.
Brown in hot (400°) oven.
Serves 8.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place in large casserole dish. Mix all ingredients. Pour over the chicken. Cover dish. Bake for 1 hour at 375°. Serve with rice.

title: grandma hatfield's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and mix thoroughly with dry ingredients.
Add raisins.
Roll out or make roll and put in refrigerator to slice.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (10 to 12 minutes).

title: gloria's quick hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese, peppers and garlic powder together. Spread on mini bagels.
Place on baking sheet and broil until spread is melted.
Watch the broiling, as some ovens are different than others and you don't want the bagels to burn.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: You will need 3 round cake pans.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Wet the crackers with milk, add the onion, crumble the hamburger into the crackers.
Mix and shape into 4 hamburger steaks.
Put into skillet that has been greased.
Cover and cook on low temperature.
Turn several times.
Cook long enough that water comes out of them.
Drain.
Add packet of beef broth to one cup of water.
Stir well and pour over steaks in skillet.
Cook until steaks are brown and the broth is cooked down.
Steaks are ready to serve.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Sift
together corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir
in
cheese.
Mix
in
egg, milk and shortening. Beat
with a rotary beater about 1 minute or until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Pour
in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: divinity salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Add pineapple with juice and marshmallows.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix and let set in refrigerator for a couple of hours or longer.
Mix in 1 pound of regular crab meat.
Serve with king size Fritos.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Drain pineapple and blot all liquid out of pineapple, onion and green pepper.
Cream all ingredients and shape into ball.
Cover with parsley leaves or nuts.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Mix all
ingredients and pour into greased baking dish. Set dish into larger pan of water to bake.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until silver knife inserted in pudding comes out clean. Serve
warm.
Top
with
vanilla ice cream if desired. Serves 6.

title: date goodies
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and dates for 8 minutes or until melted. Mix in Rice Krispies, coconut and pecans.
Roll into "fingers" or ball; roll into powdered sugar.

title: fruity smoothie "drink"
directions: Blend ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Serve in tall, frosted glass with a straw.
Garnish with a slice of an orange.

title: wanda's pepper sauce
directions: Place peppers in food processor.
Add some (not much) vinegar to keep moist or it won't cut the peppers up.
Fill a pot 1/2 full of crushed peppers.
Continue to fill pot completely full with vinegar.
Let heat.
Add mustard to color.
Keep stirring, bringing to a boil.
Pour in jars with plastic lids only.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk in pan.
Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Beat egg yolks well and stir slowly into mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Let cool.
Add raisins, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate chips, butter and corn syrup in medium size saucepan. Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and sugar. Add cereal, mixing lightly until well coated. Spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm and cut. Store in refrigerator.

title: pat's peanut butter crunch pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, eggs and milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt, vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into prepared crust.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight. Mix with other ingredients 1 hour before serving.

title: health bread dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Sift flour into large bowl.
Add salt, water and yeast.
Stir until flour is thoroughly mixed.
If dough seems too thick, add more water.
Turn out dough on floured board and knead, adding more flour, if necessary.
When dough becomes rubbery and doesn't stick to hands and board too easily, put back into bowl and brush with oil.
Let rise until double in size.
Work down and let rise again.
It is now ready to make into rolls, bread or cinnamon rolls.
Makes about 4 large loaves.

title: veracruz, chicken and rice
directions: In baking dish with cover, put rice, bell pepper and onion, cut into strips.
Pour Ro-Tel, soup and water over rice.
Salt to taste.
Sprinkle chicken with lemon pepper and lay on top of rice. Cover.
Cook in oven at 300° for 2 hours.
Stir 1/2 way into cooking.

title: nut bars
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together flour and salt; add to first mixture.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until brown, 25 minutes in 350° oven and cool.
Melt together the next 4 ingredients and cool.
Pour over the baked crust.
Press in mixed nuts and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: 20-minute potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes 14 minutes or until tender, drain.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate. Serves 6.
Preparation time:
20 minutes plus refrigerating.

title: frozen cantaloupe
directions: Heat until sugar is thoroughly melted but do not boil.
Let get very cold.
Cube melon and pour syrup over it.
Crumple waxed paper and put on top to hold melon down in syrup.
Put top on and seal tightly.
This makes enough for 5 cups.
Use 2/3 cup in each container.
Use only firm melon.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil noodles on stovetop until soft. Cook hamburger; drain grease.
In a glass dish or a 9 x 12-inch cake pan, combine all ingredients (save 1 package of Mozzarella cheese for top).
Mix well.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add a package of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Let melt.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Add bananas; mix well.

title: venison jambalaya
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add garlic powder, tomatoes, salt, pepper and venison; blend well. Stir in rice and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: pomander balls
directions: Choose desired fruit.
Use a nail or skewer to start holes for cloves, making rows all over fruit.
Decorate with strips of lace or ribbon between rows of cloves.
Add a festive bow or a sprig of mistletoe.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Roll into balls.
Brown in small amount of vegetable oil and drain.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except butter and dressing, and pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix butter and dressing. Sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll each biscuit pie in combined sugar and cinnamon.
Place pieces in greased Bundt pan.

title: turkey on the grill
directions: You will also need heavy-duty aluminum foil (can use purchased foil pan).

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Slice squash into a loaf baking pan 2/3 full.
Pour into saucepan and cover with water.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Drain well.
Add chopped onion to undiluted soup; add sour cream.
Mix with cooked squash.
Top with Stove Top stuffing.
Bake until onion and squash are tender and stuffing is brown at 350°.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serves 8.

title: quick and easy clam chowder
directions: Drain the clams, reserving the liquid to be used later.
In a soup pot, cook the salt pork until crisp.
Add the onion and cook until tender but not browned. Add the liquid (clam liquid plus water) and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are fork tender but not mushy. Add the butter and clams.
Bring to a boil and immediately reduce heat.
Gradually add half & half.
Cook over low heat until chowder thickens slightly.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add juices and pineapple.
Freeze in gallon jugs. Thaw for 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Add 2 quarts of ginger ale per gallon of punch at serving time.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In serving dish, layer:

title: orange salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add orange jello and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: italian picnic chicken
directions: Pierce chicken pieces on all sides with fork.
Place in a snug fitting bowl.
Combine olive oil, onion and garlic powders, salt and pepper in small bowl; mix well.
Pour over chicken, turning each piece to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally.

title: pork and bean dip
directions: Heat slowly until cheese is melted.
Very good with potato chips or crackers.

title: marshmallow sweet potatoes
directions: Cover sweet potatoes with boiling water and cook until soft. Peel and mash.
To every 4 cups of mashed potatoes, add a scant teaspoon of salt and 3 tablespoons butter.
Mix together.
Cover top with marshmallows and set in oven until marshmallows melt and brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese. Pour half into hot, greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle with cheese.
Add remaining mixture and bake for 25 minutes.

title: russian or spiced tea*
directions: Extract juice from oranges and lemons.
Put rind and spice in enough water to cover well and boil for 10 minutes.
Strain.
Make separately the desired amount of strong tea.
Add the spice solution and the orange and lemon juice.
Makes about 15 cups.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all desired vegetables in with spinach.
Slice bacon in small pieces; fry until crispy.
Pour over salad, mix well until spinach is a little wilted.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add onion and pepper.
Simmer until limp.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and sauce.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Put beans in crock-pot.
Pour mixture on top and mix well.
Cook 4 to 8 hours on low.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix sugar, water and pineapple; boil 3 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Stir in jello.
Place in large flat dish and jell, not too firm.
When jelled, beat cheese and Cool Whip together good. Place jello mixture, cream cheese and Cool Whip together in large dish; beat good.
Put in covered dish and re-jell.

title: toasted cheese sandwiches
directions: Broil at distance of 3-inches from flame.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Cook and cut up chicken.
Cook soup with milk.
Mix all ingredients in a large casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan, saving half of the noodles to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Add dry ingredients and stir in beans, apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
May be frosted or use whipped cream.

title: sweet roll
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool.
Add yeast to water.
Dissolve and add to milk.
Beat eggs.
Add and beat. Add flour (3 cups) and beat well.
Add remaining flour and knead. Allow to raise in greased bowl until double in size.
Punch down and shape into rolls.
Allow to raise.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen rolls.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend together sugar, salt and spices.
Combine with pumpkin. Add beaten eggs.
Stir in hot milk.
Pour into 9-inch crust.
Bake in hot oven at 425° until crust starts to brown around the edges (15 to 20 minutes).
Reduce heat to moderate oven at 350° and bake for about 30 minutes.
Do not fill pie up to top.

title: turkey and tomato pasta salad(yield:  8 cups)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a serving bowl.
Chill until serving time.

title: snowballs
directions: Combine chocolate and milk in pan over hot water.
Heat until chocolate melts.
Stir to blend.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar and walnuts.
Cool slightly and form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Makes approximately 30 snowballs.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water together slightly with a fork.
Coat pecan halves well with egg mixture.
Mix all other ingredients well and stir into nuts, coating well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300° on large cookie sheet.
Stir occasionally while cooking. Separate and cool on wax paper.
After these have cooled, store in dry airtight container.

title: oven fried mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine in small bowl mustard, lemon juice, garlic, rosemary and pepper.
Coat chicken in mustard mix. Crush bran flakes.
Add cheese.
In large (1-gallon) sealable bag, add mustard coated chicken, one piece at a time.
Shake to coat.

title: shrimp with green beans, tomatoes and feta cheese
directions: In a 10 or 12-inch skillet, heat 1 tablespoons oil over high heat.
Add shrimp and garlic and cook, tossing frequently, until shrimp are pink and loosely curled, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove shrimp to a plate.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil to skillet and, when melted, add green beans, tomatoes and wine.
Heat to boiling, stirring once or twice.
Reduce heat to medium, cover and cook about 10 minutes, until beans are crisp-tender.
Return shrimp to skillet.
Stir in lemon juice and Feta.
Cook until heated through, about 1 minute.
Serve over hot cooked rice or pasta.

title: orange muffins with smoked turkey
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease small muffin tins.
Cream the sugar and butter until smooth.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add to sugar-butter mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir until well mixed.
In food processor, grind raisins and orange zest.
Add to batter and mix.
Spoon batter into tins; bake until golden brown, about 12 minutes.
Brush tops with orange juice; sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar while still warm.
After 5 minutes, remove from pans.
Cut each muffin in half.
Cut turkey into small pieces; put small amount into each muffin.
Serves 30.

title: mom's lemon icebox pie
directions: Break eggs and separate.
Put whites in mixing bowl and save to whip for meringue.
Put yellows in another bowl and beat a little.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mix, then add lemon juice gradually.
When all is mixed, pour into a vanilla wafer crust. Whip egg whites and use as meringue.

title: sugar donuts
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Make into small balls and fry in lard until done.

title: casserole eggs
directions: Mix all together and add drained meat.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Put in a 3-quart casserole or deep jelly roll pan. Bake at 250° to 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Brown in butter.
Remove chicken; stir soup, seasonings and water into drippings.
Cook and stir to a boil.
Spread Minute rice (right from box) in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour all but 1/3 cup soup mixture over rice. Stir to moisten.
Top with chicken and rest of soup mixture. Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: buttermilk pecan waffles
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat eggs until light.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in margarine. Pour 3/4 cup butter on hot iron.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Makes 7 (8 inch) waffles.

title: tender baked chicken
directions: Coat chicken in flour with thyme, pepper and paprika in a paper or plastic bag.
Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish.
Pour gravy over chicken and bake in a preheated baking oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with additional gravy.
Serves 6.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy.
Shape dough into balls using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Top each cookie with a candy Kiss or star and press down firmly.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil the brown sugar, Karo syrup, margarine and peanuts; remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well and spread evenly in shallow pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.
Pour on waxed paper and break apart. Keeps for weeks in a covered container.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces and put a layer of cake in punch bowl.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream together and add a layer of cake then add a layer of strawberry glaze and sliced strawberries.
Continue to add layers until all mixture is used.

title: asparagus cheese bake
directions: Rinse asparagus and cut into small pieces.
Mince up the onion and then grate up your cheese.
Mix asparagus, onion, Mozzarella, Bisquick and spices together.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Beat the eggs and oil together.
Pour this over entire casserole and bake at
350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.
Serve when still warm.

title: black bean chili
directions: In a large soup pot, combine the beans, onion, kombu, water and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil, turn down heat and simmer for at least one hour.
Saute together the garlic, carrots, celery, peppers and spices.
Add to soup after the beans are fairly soft. Continue to simmer for 15 more minutes.
Add the tomatoes, shoyu, lemon juice and simmer for a final 5 minutes.
Adjust seasonings, remove bay leaves if possible and serve with freshly chopped parsley and onions.

title: chicken folders
directions: Mix margarine, flour and cream cheese.
Chill.
Roll and cut with biscuit cutter into rounds.

title: holladay buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add milk and yeast.
Knead on floured surface, making a soft dough.
Let rise until double in size.
Make into desired size buns and let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour, small amounts, and beat until all ingredients are mixed well.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: khubz(yemen bread)
directions: Mix 1 cup flour with yeast in warm water.
Cover the top of the container with a plate and keep in a warm place for 10 minutes.
In a deep, wide container, sift the flour and pour the mixture of flour and yeast and mix well, adding warm water until it is thoroughly mixed and to a slightly soft consistency.

title: popcorn mix-ups
directions: In a small saucepan, combine margarine, bouillon, curry powder and hot pepper sauce.
Cook and stir until margarine melts and bouillon dissolves.
In a large bowl, combine popcorn, pretzels and peanuts.
Toss with margarine mixture.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: chicken marsala
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and butter and cook chicken breasts for 4 minutes, turning once. Transfer to platter. Saute mushrooms, onion and garlic in same skillet for approximately 4 minutes. Add flour; mix well. Slowly stir in broth and wine. Add tarragon, pepper, bay leaves and chicken. Bring to a boil, stirring. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes until tender. Serve over pasta, noodles or rice.

title: punch
directions: Chill juices; mix together 30 minutes before serving.
Add ice cream.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar, oleo or butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Beat together well the nuts, crushed cornflakes and coconut, then add the mixture.
Mix together and drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, water and then the flour, salt and baking powder sifted together.
Pour mixture onto shallow sheet pan.
Bake in hot oven.
Spread on jelly and roll while warm.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt shortening.
Add 1 pound brown sugar and 3 eggs and mix well.
Combine and add flour, salt and baking powder.
Add chocolate chips.
Spread into 2 greased, floured sheet cake pans and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spoon in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese if desired. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease pan. Stir all ingredients until blended. Spread in pan and bake 18 to 20 minutes, until golden brown. Put fork holes in top after it cools slightly and cover with the Sweet Icing.

title: hamburger hot pot
directions: Heat large skillet to very hot.
Add ground beef and brown. Pour off any fat.
Reduce heat.
Add garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Peel and slice potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Slice onion into rings.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole, place 1/2 the potatoes, 1/2 the onion rings, then meat mixture, top with rest of potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Pour soup directly from can over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until potatoes are done.
Garnish with parsley and serve with catsup.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 2-quart dish and bake at 400° until brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Add oleo and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal in a large bowl; stir until all coated.
Add powdered sugar; mix or place lid on bowl and shake until coated.
Enjoy!

title: braunschweiger pate
directions: Blend together the liver sausage and cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, dill juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and mix well.
Stir in dill pickle and onion.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with crackers or rye bread.
Can make spread for sandwiches.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Spray casserole dish with pan.
Layer flour tortilla shells, meat sauce and cheeses until all used up.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dunkin' platter cookies
directions: In a large bowl put together the butter or margarine, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Note:
Make sure baking powder and baking soda are blended into flour before adding flour to other ingredients.
Drop onto cookie sheet in rounded teaspoons.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. These cookies spread out quite a lot in cooking, so allow lots of room between each one.

title: campfire beans
directions: Cook bacon.
Brown meat and onion.
Mix all ingredients and cook in crock-pot 3 to 4 hours or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork and veggies
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat pork chops by putting in a plastic bag with flour mixture and shaking.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in medium size skillet; add pork chops.
Saute for 5 minutes per side.
Remove to plate; keep warm.
Heat the other tablespoon of oil in skillet.
Cook onion and garlic over medium heat for 8 minutes.
Add curry powder, potatoes and chicken broth.
Cook covered for 12 minutes; reduce heat to low.
Stir in sour cream, half and half, salt, pepper and peas.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes.
Return pork to skillet; cook another minute. Serve 4.

title: child's favorite milk shake
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and blend until thick.
If shake is too thick, add 1/8 cup of milk and reblend.

title: peach cake *
directions: Mix egg, flour, baking powder and sugar, then add peaches, nuts, salt and vanilla.
Bake in a greased dish at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Can be served with 2 tablespoons of ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
A small piece of hot dog, Vienna sausage or olive can be placed in the center of the ball.
Space an inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter; spread crushed graham crackers in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover the crumbs with the melted butter. Firm the crumbs in place with hand.
Mix eggs, rest of butter and powdered sugar in bowl until creamy; beat at least 15 minutes. Spread half over cracker crumbs.
Slice bananas and cover them with rest of mixture.
Drain pineapple real good, then sprinkle over bananas until covered well.
Then cover with Cool Whip until pan is completely covered.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Chill about 3 or 4 hours before serving.

title: camper's casserole
directions: Cut dried beef.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Brown remaining beef and onion in drippings and drain.
Melt butter; add flour and blend together.
Gradually add the milk.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Combine dried beef, onion, macaroni and cheese sauce and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/4 cup dried beef.
Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: zvadly salat(wilted lettuce)
directions: Leaf lettuce is best for this dish, but head lettuce may be used.
Take 1 or 2 bunches of leaf lettuce (depends on the size of the bunch and the number of people to be served).
Take leaves apart; remove blemishes and rinse until clean.
Tear into pieces. Chop bacon; place in skillet and fry until done; remove bacon from the drippings.
Add chopped onion to taste; saute until transparent.
Return bacon to skillet and add salt to taste (it takes very little), sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Add the lettuce and lightly stir until lettuce is coated with the seasonings and is slightly wilted.
Serve at once.
A tablespoon or two of sour cream may be added.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar well.
Add unbeaten eggs and mix well. Add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavorings and mix well. Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spiced tea
