directions: Two teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water will make a delectable cup of tea.

title: taco dip
directions: In 8 x 8 baking dish, spread refried beans.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread over beans.
Sprinkle cheese on top, followed by tomatoes, green onions and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: brianna's favorite monkey bread
directions: Cut the biscuits into 4 parts and roll them into balls.
Mix 1 cup of sugar and cinnamon and roll the balls in this mixture to cover.
Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Pour a little of the butter mixture on the bottom of a Bundt pan.
Add raisins and nuts to cover.
Add half of the cinnamon balls, then more of the butter mixture.
Layer, ending with the butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Place a plate on top of Bundt pan and turn over. Serve hot.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute ground chuck, bell pepper and onion.
Add chili with beans and diced Ro-Tel.
Blend in separate saucepan and heat thoroughly, the nacho cheese soup, cream of mushroom soup (or choice) and evaporated milk.
Layer in 2 layers in large oblong (9 x 13-inch) or larger pan:
tortillas, meat mixture, soup mixture and grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Heat for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: squash-corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, squash and egg.
Pour in buttered dish.
Place cracker crumbs on top of mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake on 400° for about 30 minutes or until done in center.

title: hershey's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; mix well. Drop teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes; do not overbake.

title: mangorian
directions: Brown the hamburger in skillet with onions, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add beef bouillon, A.1. sauce, tomatoes, tomato paste (mixed with same size can of water), tomato sauce and brown sugar. Simmer all ingredients together for 1/2 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and press crushed vanilla wafers and 3/4 cup melted butter in a cake pan and bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: peach-almond pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Combine sour cream and peaches.
Add flour to butter mixture alternately with peach mixture.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour, or until done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans to cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender (cut in pieces).
Mix broccoli, mushroom soup, cheese, mayonnaise, eggs, salt and pepper in buttered dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° and serve.

title: dark fudge frosting
directions: Beat butter and add sugar, cocoa, vanilla, salt and enough milk to make rather stiff frosting.
Heat on low for about 5 minutes while stirring.
Do not boil.
Use on cakes or bars.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Place lamb in a shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roast in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes per pound. Drain crabapples, reserving 3/4 cup syrup.
Combine reserved crabapple syrup with brown sugar.
Stir to blend.
Pour some sugar mixture over lamb 30 to 45 minutes before end of roasting time. Baste lamb frequently with sugar mixture during remainder of cooking period.
Garnish with crabapples.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peanut butter heavenly hash
directions: Put chocolate chips and peanut butter in double boiler and heat until melted.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Put in 9 x 9 greased pan.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours.
Cut into squares and wrap in plastic wrap.
Store in refrigerator.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump pineapple in pan and spread evenly.
Dump pie filling over pineapple.
Dump cake mix over all. Cut margarine in thin slices and place over top.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pistachio jello
directions: Empty can of pineapple into bowl.
Sprinkle pudding over pineapple and stir until mixture thickens.
Add Cool Whip and stir until all is blended.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours or in freezer for 15 minutes.
Great for showers or potlucks.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in saucepan.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add
chopped beef (or pork), ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer until desired consistency.
Serve on buns.

title: chicken toscana
directions: Cut fryer; wash thoroughly and dry.
Salt and pepper fryer. Brown in oven at 370° for 30 minutes.
Turn so chicken browns evenly.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add pecans.
Drop by level tablespoon 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: company chicken salad
directions: Drain water chestnuts, then combine with chicken, grapes, celery and almonds.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and soy sauce in the blender.
Then toss with chicken mixture. Serve pineapple chunks separately with the salad.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Place pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix cake mix, butter and pecans until crumbly and spread on top of pie filling.
Bake at 350° until light brown and bubbly (approximately 20 minutes).

title: dill pickled okra
directions: Scrub okra and pack whole into pint jars.
In each jar, insert a few celery leaves, 1 clove garlic (peeled) and 1 sprig of dill.

title: argentina salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine lettuce, artichokes and olives in large bowl.
Combine reserved liquid, vinegar, olive oil, salt, paprika, mayo, chives and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over lettuce mixture.
Toss until well mixed.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: If pie shell is frozen, bake shell for 10 minutes at 400°. Prick sides and bottom well.
Fill the shell with the bacon, onion and grated cheese.	Over the top, pour mixture of eggs, condensed milk and half and half.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or less if brown on top.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
To this, add a mixture of eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in hot oil and cover with confectioners sugar.

title: plain soft custard
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Beat eggs; add salt, sugar and vanilla and add to milk.
Cook (bake) until it coats a spoon.

title: sugar nuts
directions: Melt 1/3 stick butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 5 to 10 minutes.

title: asparagus and parmesan salad
directions: Steam asparagus for 5 to 7 minutes or until asparagus is crisp tender.
Remove and cool slightly.
Meanwhile, for dressing, in a screw top jar, combine olive oil, lemon juice, thyme, mustard, garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and shake until combined.
Arrange asparagus on a platter.
Drizzle with dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese, parsley and if desired, basil and garlic.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables from cans and mix together with pimentos, celery, pepper and onion.
Mix sugar, oil and vinegar together and bring to a boil over high heat.
Pour over vegetables and let stand 8 hours in refrigerator.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Layer bread in a greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Top with salt, pepper, butter, onion, green pepper and sugar. Mix gently. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt, stirring well. Stir in 1/2 cup pecans and coconut.
Pour filling into unbaked pastry shell and top with remaining 1/2 cup pecans. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin
with	hot water; add cream cheese and all other
ingredients.
Add
chopped shrimp; pour into grease mold. Set for a couple of hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a large dish.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Hollow out jalapeno peppers.
Stuff with cheese.
Mix together Bisquick, sausage and leftover cheese.
Roll around each pepper. Mix eggs.
Roll armadillo egg in egg, then roll in pork Oven Fry. Bake at 325° on cookie sheet until brown for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 10 inch bundt pan with cooking spray.
In medium bowl combine both flours, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
Put pumpkin in a medium bowl.
Gradually whisk in a buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Set aside.
In a large bowl combine eggs and both sugars.
Beat well until pale in color and thickened.
With rubber spatula fold in flour mixture and pumpkin mixture (3 flour additions and 2 pumpkin additions).
Scrape into prepared pan.
Smooth surface with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: peggy hunt's bread and butter pickles
directions: Add salt to first 4 ingredients.
Cover with ice water.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain; remove garlic.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Heat to boiling.
Put in jars and seal.

title: robbie's really good jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients into batter and bake in layers in slow oven (300°) for 40 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° at end of 40 minutes and cook 5 minutes more; this browns top more.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
When mixture begins to thicken, add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine in one bowl, flour, sugar and salt.
In a saucepan, mix oleo, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix well 1 egg, margarine, cake mix and pecans; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar well until smooth.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Top should be lightly browned; center should be firm.)

title: cocoa cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Heat margarine, cocoa and cola; pour over flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and salt, blending thoroughly.
Add marshmallows.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Batter will be thick and marshmallows will float on top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour icing over hot cake.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with fork. Add mayonnaise, salt and mustard.
Mix until well blended.
Place yolk mixture back into egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: rich vanilla ice cream
directions: Prepare freezer.
In saucepan, beat eggs well; add sugar and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, just until mixture comes to boiling.
Cool, beating occasionally with rotary beater.
When cool, add cream and vanilla.
Pour into freezer can.
Freeze as directed.

title: cheese ravioli(1 pan dish)
directions: Put water and cream in a 12-inch skillet over high heat and bring to boil.
Add oil, basil and garlic.
Stir in raviolis and cover.
Uncover.
Stir and reduce heat.
Leave for 7 minutes and stir.
Add soup, vegetables, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, then add pasta.
Wait until pasta's tender.
Then serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into frying pieces.
Dip in flour.
Brown in hot grease.
Combine remaining ingredients, using 1/2 cup soup. Arrange in Dutch oven.
Pile dressing in center.
Make gravy using pan drippings and flour and enough water to make 2 cups.
Pour over chicken and dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut honey bars
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Press into a well-greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In large bowl pour Eagle Brand milk and rinse out cans.
Add water (2 cans).
Add vanilla.
Add ice cream, mix a little at a time to keep from getting lumpy, then add milk, mixing well. Pour into freezer container and add enough milk to bring to freezer line.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well and drop by spoonfuls into very hot oil.
When they start to brown, turn over in oil.
You need to use something like a deep fryer for these.

title: creamy pasta bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 10 one-cup servings.

title: wurst-beer salad
directions: In medium bowl, mix well the beer, dressing, sugar and dill seed.
Add knockwurst, potatoes and onion; toss until well coated with dressing.
Cover and chill, tossing occasionally, at least 1 hour.

title: suzy's cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Gradually add flour, then egg yolk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Put on buttered cookie sheet and pat down until 1/4-inch thick.
Put the unbeaten egg white on top. Spread all over. Press pecans down into all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into oblong pieces.

title: grandma's flour mix
directions: Mix altogether.
Good for dipping meat, chicken or rabbit, then fry.

title: michigan baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
In the morning, cover and bring to a simmer slowly, adding more water if necessary.
When beans have nearly doubled in size, stir in soda and bring to a boil.
Pour off the green liquid and put beans in a colander to drain.
Run hot water over them to clean off soda water.
Wash out the pot and put beans back in.
Cover with hot water and add the salt.
Cover and simmer until done, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Pour on buttered pan or foil.
Cool and break up into pieces.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, first chop up head of lettuce and put in.
Next layer should be your chopped up tomatoes.
Then rinse and drain your can of kidney beans and add them in.
The shredded cheese should go in next.
Take the bag of Doritos and smash them up and put on top of salad.
Wait until it is ready to be served to pour the bottle of dressing over it.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Simmer clams with juice, lemon juice, margarine, onion, oregano,
parsley, Tabasco and garlic about 5 minutes.
Add to bread
crumbs.
Spread
in	small
casserole dish.	Cover with American cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Stir milk and lemonade.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: stuffed crab
directions: Put all ingredients together and stir well.
Melt oil in large pan until hot.
Put in crab mixture and fry until real brown (about 30 minutes).

title: chocolate syrup dump cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, beating with mixer until well blended.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes or until tests done.
A very moist cake for days.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Mix wet ingredients and dressing mix; pour over vegetables. Cover and chill overnight.

title: debby's pasta salad
directions: Mix green pepper, carrots and Mozzarella cheese with pasta. Add Ranch dressing, a little at a time, stirring after each addition.
Season as desired with lemon pepper, oregano (about 6 shakes) and Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight to allow seasonings to blend.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix.
For drop cookies, chill dough first.
For bars, press ingredients into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 325° to 350° oven until set or a light brown.
Glaze while still warm with a soft mixture of powdered sugar and lemon juice or water.
Cut into squares.

title: crepes
directions: Beat all ingredients in blender.
Let stand 1 hour.
Thin, if necessary.
Pour 2 tablespoons batter into moderately heated 6-inch greased skillet.
Tilt pan to spread; fry until golden brown on each side.
Fill with whatever you like.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta, not quite done (al dente).
Add all other ingredients to cooked pasta.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: devilicious cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except sunflower seeds.
Refrigerate until firm enough to handle.
Form into a ball and roll in sunflower seeds.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 1 cheese ball.

title: italian tomato sauce with meat
directions: Heat oil in a heavy saucepan.
Add onion, celery and garlic clove (cool slightly), about 3 minutes.
Crumble ground chuck into mixture.
Brown well.
Add salt and pepper.
Clove of garlic may be removed after browning.
Add tomato paste and stir.
Add water and stir thoroughly.
Cover and let simmer over low flame (3 minutes).
Add tomato sauce, sugar, oregano, basil and garlic powder. Stir well.
Cover and simmer over flame for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Recipe is for 1 1/2 pounds of spaghetti.

title: loaf cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and apricots.
Beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Fold in nuts, if desired.
Divide in two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except noodles.
Heat in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add noodles after heating.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add liquid as needed to keep moist.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk and boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Add oats. Stir until all mixed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let set overnight.

title: puppy chow
directions: Remove powdered sugar and set aside.
Remove cereal from jar and place into a large bowl.
Place chocolate chips in a small microwave safe dish and add peanut butter.
Microwave on high for 30 seconds.
Stir.
Continue to microwave mixture for 15 seconds at a time, stirring each time until the chips are completely melted and the mixture is smooth.
Pour mixture over cereal and stir gently until the cereal is well coated.
Add powdered sugar a little at a time, stir and continue to add until well coated. Spread Puppy Chow into a single layer and allow to dry.
Store in an airtight container.

title: schnitzel(german recipe)
directions: Break eggs in a bowl.
Pour bread crumbs on a
plate and Parmesan cheese on a separate plate.
Put butter in frying pan on medium heat.
(Lots of butter.)
Soak cutlets in eggs and cover with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Do this 2 to 3 times until it has a good coating.
Fry in butter on low to medium heat until meat is done.

title: devil's float
directions: Mix the butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar, milk, flour, cocoa and vanilla in a large bowl.
Sprinkle 1 cup brown sugar, 1 cup white sugar and cocoa, mixed together, over batter, then pour the boiling water over cake and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Put soft (not melted) butter, flour and sugar into bowl.
Cut butter into mixture.
Knead with knuckles and fingertips until dough becomes round and soft and no crumbs remain.
If crumbs remain or it looks dry, it has not been kneaded enough.
(Don't use electric mixer.)
Place dough in 9 x 13-inch baking pan and flatten out evenly with back of spoon.
(Do not grease pan.)
Prick all over with fork.
Place in preheated 325° oven for about 35 minutes. Remove from oven and cut into small squares.
Lightly sprinkle top with fine coat of sugar.
Remove from pan and place on wire cake rack.
Place cookies on rack into oven at 275° for about 30 minutes.
(Watch both times, do not overbrown.)
Makes about 50 pieces.

title: indian shrimp with apples(yields 3 servings)
directions: In nonstick skillet, saute onion in hot oil with coriander, cumin, turmeric and cayenne until onions begin to brown.
Add apples and cabbage and cook over medium heat until apples begin to soften.
Stir in shrimp and cook for 3 to 5 minutes until shrimp are cooked.
Blend a little of the yogurt with cornstarch.
Then stir in the remaining yogurt.
Add to skillet and cook, stirring until mixture is hot.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.

title: pineapple cheese ball(appetizer)
directions: Drain 1/2 juice of pineapple.
Combine all ingredients.
Form into ball.
Roll in walnuts.
Chill.
Make the day before so flavors combine.

title: picnic chicken pitas
directions: In large bowl, combine broccoli, chicken, cheese and tomato. In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper; pour over broccoli mixture and toss to coat.
Spoon about 3/4 cup into each pita half.
Top with bacon if desired.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mince salmon and remove bones.
Add bread crumbs and beaten eggs and mix with milk; season with lemon juice and salt.
Pour into well-greased mold or loaf pan and steam or bake for 30 minutes at about 350°.

title: cabbage crunch salad
directions: Heat Ramen noodles, sunflower seeds and almonds in 250° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add green onions and cole slaw after heated.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Use Bundt pan.
Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Gradually add sugar.
Continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, frosting mix and pecans.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool one hour, then remove from pan.
Cool another hour before serving.

title: beet jelly
directions: Cook beets to make the juice. Use only the juice the beets were cooked in. Add Sure-Jell and bring to a boil. Then add the sugar and boil for 25-30 minutes. Remove from heat. Add the Jell-O or Kool-Aid. Stir well. Pour into jars and seal.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Cook over medium heat the sugar, water, cinnamon and allspice until mixture spins a thread when spoon is raised from the mixture.
Add the nuts and turn on low heat.
Stir all the time until sugar begins to form on the nuts.
Pour into a buttered pan and break apart.

title: pasta with cod
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Mix in tomatoes, tomato sauce, celery, salt, pepper, and oregano.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cod and cook 5 minutes.
Put half the cooked noodles in a flat pyrex dish.
Top with 1/2 of tomato/cod sauce. Repeat layers, finishing with sauce. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add grated cheese and return to oven for a few minutes.

title: pickled chix wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate chicken pieces for 3 to 4 hours.
Place chicken on cookie sheet, skin side down.
Bake 20 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.
Turn, baste with marinade and bake 20 minutes longer, until done.
Serve hot or cold.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Pour into casserole dish and cover with 1 stick melted margarine.
Top with 1 roll Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oven parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, parsley and oregano.
Brush chicken with butter.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place skin side up in an ungreased shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Bake in a 375° oven until tender, 50 to 60 minutes.
Do not turn. Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grind all ingredients 2 times.
Place in mold and refrigerate.

title: supreme chicken casserole
directions: Place half the cracker crumbs on bottom of baking dish.
Mix chicken, soups, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Dot with margarine and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Roll each chicken breast half in one slice bacon.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.
Just before serving, add mushroom pieces over them.

title: hot corned beef sandwich
directions: Break the corned beef in small pieces.
Dice the cheese to make 1 cup.
Mix all ingredients together and spread on bread or buns.
Put on a cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until heated and cheese bubbles.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: Bring the margarine and water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour, sugar and salt.
Beat in eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Pour batter into greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Batter will be thin.
Bake at 375° for 22 minutes or until cake tests done.
(Can be baked in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, molasses, syrup, coffee, melted butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine pecans and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir to mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature before cutting. Makes 6 to 8 portions.

title: manhattan meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients; roll into balls (walnut size), then put on broiler rack and put in oven for 35 to 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese, cornstarch and sugar into large bowl. Pour in drained pineapple. Place mixture into baking dish. Sprinkle Ritz crackers. Spoon melted butter over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine brown sugar, white sugar and water; stir until sugar dissolves.
Boil until threads in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Add popped corn in buttered pan.

title: black mushrooms and chicken feet soup
directions: Declaw the chicken.
Remove the main bone (tarsal) from the chicken and discard.
Cook the chicken feet in boiling water for 1 minute to clean.
Remove and rinse in cold water.
Place the chicken feet in a casserole and add remaining ingredients (except black mushrooms). Stew for 1 hour. Add the Chinese black mushrooms and stew for 15 minutes. Serve.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soups and liquid.
Pour into oblong Pyrex baking dish.
Set chicken on top, skin side up.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: aunt ada's fruit cake
directions: Add first 4 ingredients.
Add applesauce, baking soda and boiling water.
Sift flour and sugar, then add slowly to warm mixture.
Add fruits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix pudding with milk until thickened.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip. Layer a dish with graham crackers.
Add a layer of pudding, then a layer of sliced strawberries.
Add another layer of crackers, then pudding and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: tuna melt
directions: Drain tuna; place in bowl.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Spread on English muffins.
Place a slice of cheese on top of each.
Place on cookie sheet in a 350° oven until cheese is melted and muffin is lightly toasted on edges.
Careful not to burn cheese.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together, mixing pudding as directed on box.
Combine pudding, cream cheese mixture and Cool Whip. Mix well. Crumb cookies in food processor or put layer of cookies on bottom, then pudding mixture. Keep layering and end with cookies on top.
Yields 2 medium flower pots (plastic).
Put silk flower in middle and add gummy worms for decoration.

title: everything dip - vegies, crackers, etc.
directions: Mix according to your taste.
Store in covered container in refrigerator after mixing together thoroughly.
Keeps ages.

title: make the day before breakfast
directions: In a 9	x
13-inch
buttered
baking
pan, lay 8 slices bread, covering
dish completely.
Cover bread with slices of meat, then with slices of cheese and then the remaining bread slices to make it like a sandwich.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until mixture is bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in corn and eggs.
Pour in ungreased casserole.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all the ingredients and store in jars.
Use 1 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water for delicious hot beverage.

title: pineapple-coconut cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or 2 cake pans.
Heat oven to 350°.
Blend together cake mix, eggs, orange juice, oil and coconut.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes; cool for 15 minutes.
Frost with a glaze or icing.

title: quickie candy
directions: Place milk and margarine in large glass mixing bowl. Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add next 3 ingredients; mix well. Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring occasionally.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; blend well. Add oatmeal; stir until well mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls onto foil or waxed paper.
Chill until firm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain juice from all vegetables and add mayonnaise, sour cream, onion soup mix, lemon juice and hot sauce.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: jambalaya (in rice cooker)
directions: Spray cooker with Pam.
Wash rice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into rice cooker.
Lay oleo on top.
Cook until cooker goes off.

title: meat cabbage casserole
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion in butter until soft, not brown.
Add ground meat.
Cook until meat loses pink color.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer the carrots and half the cabbage. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add meat mixture.
Press down slightly.
Add remaining cabbage to spaghetti sauce.
Add Worcestershire sauce and chives; pour sauce over top of casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Add cheese on top. Bake uncovered for 5 to 8 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: raspberry cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 1/2 c. boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries and lemon juice.
(Set dish in hot water or it will harden to quickly.)
Pour into 9x13-inch pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.
Meanwhile, dissolve cherry jello in 1 c. boiling water.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Allow mixture to chill slightly. Spread sour cream over first mixture and then pour cherry-pineapple mixture over it.
Chill thoroughly.
Best if made the day before. This recipe can be cut in half by using 3 oz. pkg. of jello, 1 pkg. raspberries, 1/2 can of cranberries and 1/2 can crushed pineapple.

title: kentucky spoon bread(good with chili or ham and beans)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add last 3 ingredients and stir. Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: interstate 45 cream cheese cake
directions: Combine melted butter, 1 egg and cake mix.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gold rush brunch
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions; set aside. In saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream, parsley and potatoes.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, orange peel, nutmeg and salt.
Add to rhubarb.
Place in pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan.
Dot with butter. Adjust top crust and flute edges to make high standing rim.
Cut vents on top.
Bake in hot oven 425° for 40-50 minutes or until juices begin to bubble through vents and crust is golden brown.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in bacon fat and remove.
Boil potatoes in clam juice until just tender.
Add onion, bacon and chicken bouillon. Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not allow to boil.

title: flounder and vegetables with tarragon butter
directions: In a 1 cup glass measure, place almonds and 1 tablespoon Tarragon Butter.
Microwave on high for 1 1/2 minutes.
Set aside. In a 2-quart rectangular baking dish, stir together the beans, carrots and water.
Cover with vented plastic wrap. Stir after 7 minutes; microwave on High 10 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain and stir in 1 tablespoon Tarragon Butter.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add buttermilk	and
soda.
Stir
in dry ingredients.
Add jam last. Bake
in
3 greased and lightly floured pans, 9-inches, at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and remove from pans.

title: russian meat pie
directions: Prepare pie crust (or use ready-made crust).
Saute onion, carrots and cabbage in butter (or Pam) in large skillet, stirring often, until tender (about 15 minutes).
Remove to a large bowl. In same skillet, saute meat over high heat until it loses its pink color.
Drain.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir and simmer until slightly thickened (about 5 minutes).
Add mushroom soup (undiluted) and stir until well blended.
Remove from heat and add to vegetables.
Fit bottom pie crust into a 10-inch deep dish pie plate.
Brush this crust with the white of an egg (slightly beaten).
Spoon meat and vegetable mixture into crust.
Cover with top crust that has vents cut in it.
Brush top crust with egg yolk and 1 tablespoon water, beaten together.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Let sit for a few minutes before serving.

title: hilda's hot potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes and boil 20 minutes. Drain and reserve liquid. To potatoes, add chopped onion, chopped eggs, chopped pickles, cubed butter, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper. Beat on high until well blended. Salad should be moist and creamy. Add reserved liquid in small amounts if too dry. Taste and amend with a tad more vinegar if needed.
Serves approximately 35 people.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Blend in macaroni. Bake in greased casserole, uncovered, until brown and bubbly.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter in skillet or blazer pan of chafing dish, blend in flour.
Add cream all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Place hot water bath under blazer pan if using chafing dish.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture, cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add lobster, heat.
Add wine, lemon juice and salt.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve in patty shells.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, squeeze out water and chop.
Mix with all other ingredients and chill for 1 hour.
Great with Triscuits or any other favorite cracker.

title: frozen cabbage slaw
directions: Mix salt and cabbage; let stand one hour in water to cover. Drain well. Add carrot and pepper.

title: raspberry shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and turn to high speed.
Blend for 45 seconds, or until creamy and smooth.

title: cheri's bean salad
directions: Mix liquids and seasonings together.
Pour over beans and olives.
Let set in refrigerator at least 4 hours.
May be kept in refrigerator for 2 weeks, if stored tightly covered.

title: marinade for flank steak or pork tenderloin
directions: Marinate 3 to 4 pounds of flank steak or a 3 to 4 pound pork tenderloin for 24 hours.
Bake or roast.
Yields marinade for 3 to 4 pounds of meat.

title: atkelt alecha
directions: Boil carrots, string beans and potatoes separately in enough water to cover each.
Boil carrots and potatoes about 15 minutes, beans about 10 minutes.
In Dutch oven, heat oil.
Saute onion until brown.
Add cardamon, ginger, garlic and salt to taste; stir well to blend.
Add vegetables.
Let simmer about 3 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: magic middle cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking cocoa and baking soda in small bowl.
Cream margarine, 1/4 cup crunchy peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Combine powdered sugar and 3/4 cup crunchy peanut butter in a small bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Shape chocolate mixture around peanut butter balls covering completely.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until slightly cracked.

title: sandra's baked rice
directions: Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, oil, vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients to oil mixture together with zucchini in small amounts.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Pour even amounts into each pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and sugar together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: lemon buttermilk cake
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 9
x 13-inch pan.
In bowl mix cake mix and 2 eggs.
Press
in	bottom	of
pan.
Mix
cream cheese, powdered sugar and	2 eggs along with lemon flavoring. Pour on top of cake mix and
eggs.
Bake
at
350° for 35 minutes.

title: rich sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine yeast and remaining ingredients in bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Dough will be very soft. Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Shape as desired.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Soften butter and combine with flour and sugar.
Blend on low until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Place 2 3/4 cups of mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
To the remaining mixture, add soda, salt, cinnamon, egg, sour cream and vanilla.
Blend well.
Stir in apples, spoon evenly over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: *uncooked fudge
directions: Mix together sugar and eggs.
Melt together chocolate and butter.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Place in buttered pan.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: fonduloha
directions: Select pineapple with fresh green leaves.
Cut each pineapple lengthwise in half through green top, then cut in half again, making 4 pieces each with part of the green top.
Remove fruit by cutting along edges with a curved knife.
Cut fruit into cubes, removing any eyes and fibrous core.
Drain pineapple shells, cut side down.

title: mushroom logs
directions: Separate rolls into 8 rectangles; press perforations to seal. Combine cream cheese, mushrooms and seasoning salt; mix well. Spread mushroom mixture in equal portions over each rectangle of dough.
Starting at long side, roll up each rectangle jellyroll fashion; pinch seam to seal.
Slice logs into 1-inch pieces; place seam side down on an ungreased baking sheet.
Brush each log with beaten egg and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburger meat and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer for 20 minutes.
I usually serve with macaroni.

title: fried cabbage and noodles
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan that has a tight-fitting lid. Saute onion until tender.
Add cabbage.
Cover and cook over low heat until cabbage is tender.
Add noodles and mix with cabbage and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, butter and cream cheese.
In a separate bowl, blend the Cool Whip, pudding mix and milk.
Blend both mixtures together.
In a clean flower pot, layer cookies and mix.
Make sure to put cookies on bottom and top.
Refrigerate.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Blend in egg, vanilla and milk.
In a separate bowl, sift together dry ingredients, except oats and raisins.
Stir dry ingredients into first mixture.
Stir in oats, then raisins.
Beat well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pronto pizza
directions: Roll out biscuits onto pizza pan.
Mix tomato sauce, onions, oregano and garlic salt.
Pour onto rolled out dough and sprinkle the 2 cheeses on top and bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: layered salad
directions: Chop lettuce and cauliflower and mix in large salad bowl. Mix in shredded cheese, bacon bits and peas. Add mayonnaise and Italian dressing. Mix well. Refrigerate a little before serving.

title: mom edwards' pink cherry specialty cake
directions: Combine
and sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Drop in shortening and mix together.
Combine milk with cherry juice. Add a little at a time.
Beat.
Add vanilla and almond extract. Beat
in
egg
whites.
Fold
in
cherries and nuts. Bake at
375° for 20 to 25 minutes (8-inch round pans).
When cooled, top with whipped whip cream (can tint pink).

title: cake mix brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together (batter will be stiff).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan. Bake at 350° until done.
Can be frosted.
Nuts can also be added, if desired.

title: good chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts in one quart of water.
Pick meat off the bones.
Add 2 cans butter beans, 1 can stewed tomatoes and 1 can tomato sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste; simmer for awhile.
Add chopped onion, frozen mixed veggies and potatoes.
Cook on low for at least another hour.
This makes a really big pot full of good soup.

title: pepperoni and cheese loaf
directions: Thaw dough and allow to rise according to package directions. Divide dough in half and set one portion aside.

Turn out remaining portion of dough on a lightly floured surface. Roll dough into a 10-inch circle. Combine egg and Parmesan cheese, stirring well; spread half of egg mixture over circle, leaving a 1/2 inch margin at edges. Layer half of pepperoni and half of Mozzarella cheese over egg mixture; sprinkle with half of oregano. Roll up dough and seal edges. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Blend well, then add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Last, add nuts.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pineapple temptation
directions: In a large bowl, let ice cream and sherbet soften slightly at room temperature.
Add juices and 1 tablespoon rind.
With egg beater or electric mixer at low speed, beat until frothy.
Add ginger ale; beat slightly until foamy.
Serve in chilled glasses, garnished with rest of rind and mint.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit and cabbage slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: chocolate chip meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a small bowl at high speed, beat egg whites with salt until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mixture should be glossy and very stiff.
Stir in vanilla and fold in chips.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 25 minutes or until cookies are light golden and firm to touch.
Let cookies cool on a plate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Saute pepper, pimento and onion until tender in margarine. Add to cream and Cheddar cheese.
Blend with mixer until smooth. Roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate (covered).
Leave out several hours to soften.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, margarine, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and milk. Cut the butter into bottom of baking dish.
Pour in mixture. Top with fruit and bake at 350° until browned on top and bubbly.

title: crunchy fish fillets(microwave)
directions: In glass pie plate, melt butter on High for 30 to 45 seconds; stir in lemon juice, parsley and tarragon.
In another flat dish, combine corn flakes, almonds, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat fillets with seasoned butter, then crumb mixture.
Arrange in cooking dish and cover with paper towel.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, turning every 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat for 5 minutes on medium speed. Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Bake in floured and greased tube pan.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking or roasting pan; discard bag.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Chill completely and serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: old-fashioned rice custard
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1-quart baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Stir in rice and raisins.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Set dish in a pan filled with enough hot water to come halfway up sides of dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir mixture to bring rice to the top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and dot with butter. Return to oven.
Bake an additional 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Fold milk and cool whip together.
Add pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Mix well and chill.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease pie plate. Beat all ingredients until smooth, abut 1 minute on high. Pour into pie plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Dip bananas in 7-Up.

title: mushroom dressing
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in margarine until onion is golden.
Add stuffing mix to boiling water.
Toss all together and mix well.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles. Mix ingredients. Put in a casserole dish. Add 1/2 cup cheese on top of mixture. (I use Mozzarella and Cheddar.) Crush Ritz crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: avocado salad
directions: Mash avocado with fork.
Add other ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	according
to
directions;
set
aside. Cook 6 servings of rice;
set aside.
Put Cheez Whiz, soup and butter together and melt.	Then add mushrooms and cooked rice. Put broccoli
in
casserole dish.
Pour the other mixture over it. Cook at 350° until edges bubble.
Watch carefully.

title: festive english trifle
directions: Carefully split cake and fill with desired preserves.
Cut into small pieces about 1 1/4-inches in diameter.
Place one layer of cake pieces in glass bowl.
Strain fruit cocktail, reserving juice.
Add layer of fruit cocktail to bowl, then repeat layers. Prepare Jell-O using only one cup of boiling water at first.
Then add cream sherry and reserved fruit juice.
Add enough cold water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Pour over cake and fruit cocktail. Allow to chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream, cherries cut in half and nuts.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground beef and onion.
Put in baking dish.
Put mushroom soup over ground beef.
Put cheese on top of soup.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until good and brown.

title: eggnog
directions: In a blender or with a beater, mix ice cream, eggnog and liquor.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Grade cheese fine and cream with butter. Add dry ingredients; roll to 1/4 inch thick, cut in strips. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8-10 minutes. Let cool. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: frozen molded salad or dessert
directions: Mix all.
Pour into paper liners in muffin tins 3/4 full. Makes 14 to 15.
Freeze.
Pull off paper.
Store in freezer in bag until needed.
Serve slightly thawed on fresh lettuce as side salad or as dessert garnished with 1 cup whipped heavy cream sweetened with 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar or 1 teaspoon honey.
Top with fresh strawberries, crushed and sweetened with honey.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip and pour into shell.
Decorate top with your favorite fruit.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream shortening, add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour, soda and nutmeg several times.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Add flavorings and pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zesty italian crescent casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Heat until hot and bubbly.
Pour into ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon cheese over meat mixture.
Separate crescent rolls into rectangles and place on top of casserole.
Combine Parmesan cheese and butter.
Crumble evenly over dough.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 25 minutes or until deep golden brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix and shape using teaspoon.
Melt butter in large heavy skillet. set over medium heat.
Fry meatballs to brown on all sides.
Remove skillet from heat.
Sprinkle flour evenly over meatballs, stirring to blend well.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water, add to pan.
Stir in remaining evaporated milk and worcestershire sauce.
Return pan to low heat and cook.
Stir frequently until gravy is thickened.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: elephant ears
directions: In a saucepan combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening; heat until shortening is melted.
Do not let boil.
Cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Stir in flour, two cups at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Put in a greased bowl.
Cover with a damp cloth and let rise until doubled (about 30 minutes).

title: santa fe stew
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onion, drain it off.
Pour taco seasoning and ranch seasoning.
Stir well.
Put in Dutch oven or pot and add all other ingredients and cook until hot.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook whole sweet potatoes in boiling water 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.

title: green salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Be sure to get the pudding well mixed.
Refrigerate.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift together baking powder, baking soda, salt and flour.
Add sugar, gradually and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas, a small amount at a time.
Beat well after each addition until smooth.
Pour into a well-greased pan 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine in mixing bowl eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat well with fork.
Blend evaporated milk into mixture.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Melt butter and stir in peanut butter.
Stir until smooth and add sugar.
Remove from heat and roll into balls.
Dip in chocolate and eat!

title: coconut pie
directions: Let oleo soften and cream together with sugar.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Add milk, vanilla and 3/4 of coconut. Sprinkle remaining coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix by shaking up in a paper bag.
Add chocolate, if needed, or add sugar or sweetener.
Fill a cup about 1/3 to 1/2 full.
Add boiling water and stir.
May be warmed in microwavable cup.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti in lightly salted water.
Mix everything together.
Let stand overnight.
Optionally one can add fresh mushrooms and/or sliced ripe olives.

title: ozark honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased sheet; flatten with bottom of glass that has been greased and dipped in sugar.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: sweet and sour tuna
directions: Heat margarine until foamy.
Add celery and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in tuna, pineapple, chicken broth or bouillon cube, vinegar, soy sauce and pepper.
Heat thoroughly. Blend in a mixture of 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup cold water. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: mama martin's sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
With rotary mixer, blend sweet potatoes and margarine until smooth.
Beat in other ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook until tender and can be torn apart easily.
Be sure you have enough water to make your broth to cook the dumplings in.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine baking mix and 1/4 teaspoon of the garlic powder; mix in cheese.
Add milk, stirring just right until dry ingredients are moistened.
Roll or pat dough on a lightly floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 1 1/2-inch cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Combine melted butter and the remaining 1/8 teaspoon of the garlic powder; brush on tops of biscuits and bake for 10 minutes, or until golden.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Arrange bananas and wafers.
Pour mixture over each layer.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water; add boiling water and sugar. Cool.
Then add sour cream, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Pour into ring mold and chill until set.
Unmold and fill center with fresh strawberries.

title: green bean roll-ups
directions: Roll 8 to 10 green beans in 1/2 slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Combine other ingredients and pour over green beans. Marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Brush brisket with liquid smoke. Cover with foil and bake at 275° four or five hours.

title: pecan squares
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: double chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips, sugar, applesauce and margarine in large heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add egg whites; stir well.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 16 to 20 minutes, or just until set. For fudgier brownies, bake to minimum baking time.
Cool completely.
Makes 24 brownies.
Each contains 7 grams of fat versus 11 grams in traditional recipe.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil.
Make meat balls 1 to 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Fry in oil until brown on all sides.
When done, set aside.

title: lemon rum pudding
directions: Combine gelatin and pudding mix in saucepan; add water, mixing well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Chill until thickened.
Blend in vanilla, rum extract and nutmeg.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour gelatin mixture into mold or decorative dishes.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold. Makes approximately 10 servings.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper. Scramble eggs in sausage mixture. Fill shells with meat and egg mixture; top with cheese and salsa. Roll tortilla and serve.

title: pie crust
directions: With fork, mix first 4 ingredients.
In a separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Then with hands, mold dough into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling it out into desired shape.
Dough can be left in refrigerator up to 3 days or frozen until used.
Makes 2 (9-inch) double pie crusts and 1 (9-inch) pie shell.

title: bologna salad
directions: Mix together and make sandwiches or eat on Ritz crackers.

title: tender round steak(in a crock pot)
directions: Put steak in bottom of crock pot. Stir vegetables, seasonings and soup together in large bowl and pour over meat. Add water to cans and pour into crock pot if needed to cover meat and vegetables. Cover. Cook on low 8 hours.

title: key lime bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease an 8 x 8 inch pan. Mix 1 cup flour and confectioners sugar; add butter, and pat into pan. Bake 15-20 minutes.

title: krumkaker
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Beat eggs and sugar well.
Then add vanilla, cardamom, butter and flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Put batter on krumkake iron with teaspoon.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 to 40 seconds.
Remove and quickly shape into cones or on a stick.

title: sausage and grits casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain well.
Cook grits 5 minutes in boiling salted water.
Add butter and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add eggs, milk and sausage.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan, combine soups, sour cream and cream cheese.
Heat on low until cheese is melted.
Pour 1/3 of sauce over broccoli; add a layer of noodles and chicken.
Add a second layer of 1/3 of sauce, noodles and chicken.
Finish with 1/3 of sauce.
Put 1 1/2 cups of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy deviled eggs
directions: Shell 6 hard-cooked eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove egg yolks.
Mash yolks.
Blend with zesty hot dog relish, mayonnaise and salt.
Spoon into egg whites, chill and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: elephant ears
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the water over part of the mixture and gently toss with a fork.
Push to the side.
Repeat until all is moistened, then put on a lightly floured surface.
Roll out like you were making a pie, but try to go oblong, then just cut into squares and put on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Let cool.

title: dorito pie
directions: Brown meat; add onion, chili powder, tomatoes, soup and milk. In large baking dish, layer half of Doritos, meat/soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange breakfast drink
directions: Put in blender and fill with ice cubes. Mix well and serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool completely.
Boil eggs and cool completely.
In large bowl, chop potatoes and eggs into small cubes.
Add sweet pickles, pickle juice, Miracle Whip, prepared mustard and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: hillbilly casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Mix the catsup, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add all the beans.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Slice squash, pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Saute in butter or margarine. Drain.
Set vegetables aside.
Combine mayonnaise and cheese together.
Line pie shell with tomato slices. Top with vegetables, then top with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Place chopped cauliflower in salad bowl.
Add mixed dressing. Stir until well combined.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Grate all cheese in bowl.
Add chopped onions and enough mayonnaise to spread easily.
Spread cheese mixture on French rolls that have been sliced very thin.
Put rounds in broiler, about 6 inches under fire until cheese has a slight toasted look (approximately 2 minutes).
Serve immediately.

title: candied red apples
directions: Will also need 10 to 12 wood skewers.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Mix together water and oleo; let cool.
Add flour to water and oleo gradually.
Add eggs one at a time; beat after each egg. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan (batter will be thin).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together the pudding mix and milk.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese. Stir until cheese is melted.

title: dilly shrimp dip
directions: Place cottage cheese, cream cheese, dill, onion and lemon juice in food processor or blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Spoon mixture into bowl and stir in shrimp.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: breading
directions: You will need three bowls.
In one bowl, mix eggs, water and salt and pepper.
In a second bowl, put flour.
In third bowl, bread crumbs.
Whatever you are breading, start with dipping into flour, turning to insure all parts covered with flour.
Then dip into egg mixture.
Let drip a little and finally dip into bread crumbs. You should press the bread crumbs down into whatever you are breading so the crumbs will adhere.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Mash pulp; stir in oleo, 1 1/2 cups of cheese, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Stuff shells with potato mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mustard
directions: Mix first two ingredients and let stand overnight.
Cook next three ingredients 30 to 40 minutes (until thick) with the mustard and vinegar.
Let cool.
Add 1 1/2 cups mayonnaise.
Keep refrigerated.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla in small saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick, about 12 minutes. Stir in coconut and pecans.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
This is an excellent frosting for a chocolate cake or chocolate cupcakes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients
and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well. Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternating with sour cream.
Start and end with flour.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: easy cake
directions: Cook 1 package chocolate pudding by package directions.
Blend in one box dry chocolate cake mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips (and nuts if desired).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread croutons in bottom.
Sprinkle sausage over croutons.
Pour milk mixture over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove and let stand 30 minutes. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel hard-boiled eggs.
Cut in halves.
Put yolks in mixing bowl and mix in ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Put in halves and sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Make graham cracker crust and press in bottom of baking dish, reserving 1/4 cup crumbs for top.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 1/3 cups boiling water; stir in sugar.
Allow to cool and become slightly set.
Whip well chilled evaporated milk.
Add Jell-O mixture to whipped evaporated milk; whip until stiff.
Add juice and grated rind of 2 lemons or 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Spread over crumb crust.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and refrigerate.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Layer in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine all other ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Pour into casserole on top of spaghetti.
Dot with butter or margarine. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs. Peel and put in large jar. Sun tea jug works great. Boil water, sugar, vinegar and pickling spice for 5 minutes. In a sun tea jug, pour beets in jug. Add peeled, boiled eggs. Pour boiled mixture over beets and eggs. Eggs should be pickled in 3 days.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute your onions and margarine.
Add the rest of the ingredients and heat until warm.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add the next 6 ingredients; simmer, uncovered, until thick (about 1 hour).
Cook the lasagna noodles in boiling water until tender; drain noodles and rinse in cold water.

title: onion, pepper and tomatoes for white rice
directions: Use amount needed for your family.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Peel cucumbers and cut lengthwise, taking out seeds. Grate cucumbers and onions. Add salt and pepper. Add vinegar and let set 30 minutes. Put mixture in colander and drain all liquid. Add cream cheese and mayonnaise; mix well.

title: dudley's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add baking powder, vanilla, milk and flour.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet; flatten with fingers.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown around edges. Cookies are better if they are not brown on top.
Yields about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: lemon pie cake
directions: Make lemon pie mix first; let cool, using 2 packages pie filling, as directed.
Use sugar as for 1 box; use 3 1/2 cups boiling water.

title: best and easiest next-morning coffee cake
directions: Grease tube pan with margarine or Crisco.
Place individual rolls around bottom of pan.
Drizzle melted margarine over rolls. Combine pudding, brown sugar and nuts and sprinkle over rolls. Sprinkle rolls with cinnamon.
Cover and leave at room temperature overnight to allow rolls to rise.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: stir-fry chicken and vegetables
directions: In bowl, combine chicken broth, cornstarch, soy sauce, garlic, ginger and orange peel.
Blend and set aside.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the margarine and peanut butter.
Beat in sugars.
Stir in 1 egg, salt and vanilla. Arrange by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Press flat with fork.
Bake until firm (about 10 minutes).
Makes approximately 60 cookies.

title: chicken salad on buns
directions: In a bowl, combine the first six ingredients; mix well.
Spoon about 1/3 cup onto each roll.
Wrap each tightly in foil.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter in microwave.
Stir and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat broccoli to boil.
Add cheese and butter and let melt. Mix together cream, soup, rice, onion and crackers.
Add broccoli mixture together with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and oil.
Mix well. Add sifted flour to mixture and stir.
Put dough on floured surface and knead several times.
Roll out and cut into biscuits. Let rise 45 minutes to 1 hour in greased baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 10 biscuits.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa good.
Boil with salt and cream 7 minutes. Add margarine and marshmallow cream.
Beat until thick.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: fig cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add oil and beat again.
In another bowl, mix dry ingredients well.
Put 1/2 dry mixture into egg, oil and sugar mixture.
Next, add 1 cup figs and mix well. Add last of dry mixture.
Add pecans and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon-glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut in half lengthwise.
Cover with salt and enough boiling water.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Stir in sugar and lemon.
Add carrots; stir until well glazed over medium heat. Makes 6 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook to the soft ball stage.
Cool until bubbles subside, then pour over popcorn and stir.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together.
Put in the bottom of a pan (mixture will be sticky).
In blender, mix pumpkin, 4 eggs, brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: southwestern meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°
Combine the first 8 ingredients. Spread into an ungreased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: quick hearty bean soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a large soup pot, bring to a boil on high, then reduce heat to a gentle simmer until onion, potato, celery and turnip are done, roughly 35 to 40 minutes.
We do not add salt since other ingredients do very nicely for seasoning. This makes six generous helpings and with the addition of a hot bread and a light dessert makes a meal.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Boil milk and sugar.
Stir in the flour, cornstarch and cocoa.
Beat eggs and pour hot pudding over eggs, stirring well. Cool; add the cream, brown sugar and vanilla.

title: venison steaks
directions: Drop steaks in boiling water.
Let stay until they turn white. Remove and beat in salt and pepper.
Roll in flour and fry like chicken.

title: mexican hot corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Line a cast-iron skillet with foil; spray with Pam.
Pour in 1/2 batter; cover this with the cheese.
Add the rest of the batter, covering with cheese well. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until center is firm and done.
Cut in small cubes and serve warm or room temperature.

title: fried indian bread
directions: Mix well.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Roll out thin.
Cut in squares.
Fry in hot oil.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Grease four No. 303 cans.
In a large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients, except nuts and cherries.
Spoon into cans and bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.

title: instant pudding salad
directions: Sprinkle dry pudding over fruit.
Mix well, then add bananas and any of the other optional fruit you choose.
Mix well and serve.

title: that's it salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in pineapple (no water).
Mix cottage cheese in thoroughly, then mix in Cool Whip.
Let set.
That's it! (Chopped nuts may be added.)

title: pepper relish(carrie kneisley)
directions: Grind peppers and onions together with a handful of salt.
Add boiling water enough to cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Can.

title: mexican quiche appetizers
directions: Mix the cheeses in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour eggs over the cheeses.
Sprinkle with chilies.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until set.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Place on crisp crackers or taco chips.

title: fresh garden salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Rinse in cold water. Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together graham cracker crumbs, sweetened condensed milk, chocolate pieces and nuts.
Spread evenly in a greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven 25 to 30 minutes.
While still warm carefully cut into squares.
Cool in pan.
Makes about 25 cookies.

title: lime pudding
directions: Mix Jell-O, hot water, sugar and lemon juice; refrigerate until beginning to thicken.
Mix in Dream Whip, mixed according to directions.
Add coconut.
Pour over cubed angel food cake.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift the sugar to get out lumps.
Sift the cake flour five times before measuring.
Beat the egg whites with salt until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and continue beating until eggs are stiff, but not dry.
Fold in the sugar and add flavoring.
Fold in flour, one tablespoon at a time.
Bake in ungreased angel food pan in very slow oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cream cheese taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add sour cream gradually, mixing with mixer.
Add bean dip and taco seasoning; beat on low speed until well mixed.
Place in a shallow casserole dish and top with Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, until thoroughly heated.
Serve with Doritos or dip-size Fritos.

title: lana's double fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and salt to soft ball stage in a 3-quart heavy saucepan over medium heat, stirring continuously. Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: warwick molded salmon
directions: Combine milk and crumbs and cook until texture is smooth. Flake salmon; remove skin and bones.
Combine milk mixture, salmon, eggs, salt and lemon juice and pour into an oiled loaf pan (approximately 5 x 9-inch).
Place filled loaf pan in a larger pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Unmold and serve with cucumber sauce.

title: red punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 1 gallon.
Put into quart containers and freeze.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients and add remaining ingredients. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 small pies or 1 large one.

title: swedish chicken breast
directions: Place dried beef in bottom of large casserole dish.
Put chicken breasts, wrapped in bacon, on top of dried beef.
Mix celery soup, mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and bake at 250° for about 4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Cut slices of dried beef into small pieces.
Combine cream cheese, dried beef pieces, onion chips and Accent in a large bowl; mix well.
Use more onion chips and Accent if needed.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Boil until tender.
When cool, remove skins.
Split potatoes lengthwise.
Place in baking pan and sprinkle with brown sugar and pieces of butter on each potato. Moisten sugar with plenty of cream and add little boiling water in bottom of pan.

title: caramels
directions: Bring sugar, butter and corn syrup to boil in saucepan, stirring, then boil 4 minutes without stirring.
Remove pan from heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk; mix well.
Return pan to heat; cook at medium-low boil for 30 minutes, or until mixture reaches 238° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool in pan 2 hours.
Remove from pan; cut into 1-inch pieces with very sharp serrated knife.
Wrap each piece in wax paper.
Makes approximately 40 caramels.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Bake.
Cook flour and milk, stirring constantly, until thick.
Let cool. Cream sugar, 1 stick of margarine and Crisco.
Add to cooled flour mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat together like whipped cream.
Spread on cake and refrigerate overnight.

title: pie crust
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together the flour, salt and sugar. Cut in chilled butter until crumbly. Mix in just enough water (with a fork) to moisten flour. Shape dough into a ball, flatten and roll out on lightly floured surface into a 12-inch circle. Place in a 9-inch pie pan and flute or crimp edges. Bake in 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown or fill and bake as directed.

title: my mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells (2). Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: tang salad
directions: Drain pineapple to have 1 cup juice.
Mix juice, Tang and pudding, then add fruit.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill.

title: chicketti
directions: In a big bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix together and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°. Let sit 15 minutes before serving.

title: glazed rutabagas
directions: Wash rutabaga and pare thinly.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat butter in a 10-inch skillet until melted.
Add rutabagas.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, stirring frequently until light brown on all sides, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, water and salt.
Cover and simmer over low heat stirring occasionally until tender, about 20 minutes.

title: snickerdoodle cookies(my kids love these; great for dunking in milk.)
directions: Crush cookies to crumbs and put half in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Save other half.
Beat together cream cheese, Cool Whip and margarine.
In a separate bowl, beat pudding, milk, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Combine bowls of ingredients.
Pour over Oreo crumbs.
Top with remaining crushed Oreos.
Refrigerate.

title: extra special carrots
directions: Cook carrots to tender-crisp stage, 10 minutes or so.
Bring sugar and vinegar to boil.
Add tomato soup, oil, mustard, Worcestershire and salt.
Cook just long enough to blend.
Layer carrots in 1 1/2-quart or larger container.
Put onion and pepper on top.
Continue until all vegetables are used.
Pour sauce over all and refrigerate at least 24 hours to blend flavors.
Will keep 3 weeks.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix together ingredients well.
Bake in cake pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost with caramel icing.

title: cinnamon honey spread
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Spread on apple bread.

title: party meatballs
directions: Spread meat out and sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Put bread in large mixing bowl and pour milk over it. Place meat in bowl with bread and mix thoroughly.
Shape into small meatballs.
Place in baking dish.
Mix jelly and chili sauce, pour over meatballs.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Chop celery, onion and carrots; saute in margarine until tender.
Add spices.
Cook 4 cups potatoes in 1 cup water until soft.
Add sauted vegetables, spices and prepared instant potatoes.
To all this, add milk.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook on low heat for 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. In another bowl, whisk the eggs, add pumpkin, cranberries and butter. Stir in dry ingredients until well mixed. Put into a
15 x 10 x 1 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: meal in a kettle
directions: Combine all ingredients in large cooker.
Cook on medium heat until done.

title: scallops in wine
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion until tender (about 5 minutes).
Add scallops, mushrooms, wine, water and lemon juice.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and cook until scallops are just tender (about 15 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, blend flour, salt and cream; gradually stir into scallop mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Spoon mixture onto heated plates, sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fold in Cool Whip and sour cream; freeze.

title: fiery turkey thighs
directions: Rinse turkey thighs.
Pat dry.
Peel and chop onion.
In a skillet, heat margarine.
Add turkey thighs and saute until browned on all sides (about 15 minutes).
Add onion and saute a few more minutes.
Sprinkle with salt, paprika and flour.
Stir to combine.
Cover.
Cook over medium-low heat about 25 minutes, turning thighs from time to time.
Cut thighs into halves.
Add sour cream and chili peppers.
