Blend well and cook for another 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped chives.
Good served with rice or noodles.
Serves 8.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Add seasonings, tomato sauce, tomatoes (chopped) and water.
Add beans and simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: anna's danish raisin, brown bread
directions: Boil raisins and water 1 minute.
While hot, add Crisco and cool.
Add sugar, soda, salt, egg and molasses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and scallops
directions: Sprinkle sherry, salt and pepper over seafood in casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix onion, garlic, parsley and oregano with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of seafood.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes (not too long; shrimp and scallops cook fast.)

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in coconut, raisins, pecans, salt and vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Bake for 25 minutes longer.
Yields 8 servings.

title: no roll sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar, confectioners sugar and oleo. Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measure cup.
Level off.
Stir dry ingredients into sugar mixture. Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until set, but not brown.
Makes 5 to 7 dozen.

title: grandma's banana split cake
directions: Cook at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: french breakfast doughnuts
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until all is moistened.
Put in greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring Crisco and water to a boil.
Add flour and salt all at once to boiling water and Crisco.
Stir until mixture leaves sides of pan, about 30 seconds.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating with beater after each egg.
Put on greased (waxed paper) cookie sheet, about 1/4 cup to each puff.
Leave plenty of room, they rise big. Bake for 10 minutes at 450° and 20 minutes at 400°.
Fill with pudding that is cooled.
Sprinkle xxxx sugar.

title: cherry delight
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with whole graham crackers, breaking if necessary to fill pan.
Combine pudding mix and milk in bowl. Beat slowly at lowest speed of electric mixer until well blended. Let stand about 5 minutes.
Blend in whipped topping.
Spread half the pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers. Top with remaining mixture and then another layer of crackers. Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill about three hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn, milk, egg and onion salt in a 1-quart casserole. Combine cornflake crumbs and cheese; spread over corn mixture. Bake in Radarange oven on Cookmatic level 5 (slow cook) for 15 to 18 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cranberry fruit-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir in orange juice, orange peel, shortening and egg; mix until well blended.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Turn into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased on bottom only.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and cinnamon.
In saucepan, put oil, water, butter and cocoa and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Mix together eggs, vanilla and buttermilk and add to batter.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased sheet pan and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and rice-a-roni
directions: Combine in a large baking dish 2 1/2 cans of water, the 2 cans of soup and the special seasoning from the Rice-A-Roni box; mix well.
Layer cut up chicken in center of dish.
Pour the remaining Rice-A-Roni ingredients all around chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue for sandwich
directions: Cook fresh picnic ham (can be cooked on covered grill or in oven).
Let cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Form into a loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Combine 1/4 cup ketchup with pineapple; spoon over loaf.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt, spices and white sugar. Put Crisco in mixer bowl, stir to soften.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to soften Crisco.
Add brown sugar. Beat and add eggs and beat well.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: greek style chicken
directions: Mix lemon juice and spices together and set aside.
Cut potatoes in small pieces and place on one side of 9 x 13-inch pan. Dip leg quarters in lemon juice mixture.
Place chicken on the other side of pan.
Pour remaining mixture over potatoes and chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package; remove from oven and break into small pieces.
Mix chocolate mousse according to package.
In a large glass bowl, place pieces of brownies in bowl until bottom is covered (approximately 1/2 of crumbled brownies), then spread half of the chocolate mousse mixture over the brownies.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip; sprinkle chopped Heath bar over top.
Continue layering with remaining ingredients, ending up with Cool Whip and chopped Heath bar on top.

title: valentine cherry jello punch
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients to liquid jello.
Serve in punch bowl.
Portions of punch may be poured into ring mold.
Red and green cherries can be added and ring frozen.
Unmold and float in punch.
Makes about 100 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip together.
Add cinnamon and sugar to taste.
Start off and add more to taste if desired.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients; add flour, baking soda and salt into sugar mixture.
Fold in quick oats and corn flakes. Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300 degrees for 7-8 minutes or until light brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2 qt. casserole, stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave on high for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and microwave on high for 3 to 5 minutes till light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blend and microwave on high for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: scallop soup
directions: Saute scallops in butter with garlic.
While sauteing scallops, dice celery, carrots and onions.
Heat chicken broth.
Add seasonings, vegetables and scallops.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer and cook for about 45 minutes (until vegetables are tender enough to be pierced with a fork).
Add half and half.
Cook approximately another 15 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch to desired thickness.

title: creamed onions
directions: Peel onions and cook
in large amount of boiling salted water until tender (about
to
minutes).	Drain.	Melt butter in large saucepan;
add
flour and blend.
Stir in milk and cook slowly until thick, stirring constantly.
Add onions. Heat through for
several
minutes
and	serve.	Garnish
with parsley or paprika.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and confectioners sugar.
Add yolk and vanilla. Beat well.
Add flour.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with palm of hand.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with icing.

title: spinach patties
directions: Defrost spinach patties and drain water.
Add 5 or 6 heaping tablespoonfuls of flour, garlic powder, Parmesan cheese and egg. Stir until mixed well.
Will be kind of watery.
Cover bottom of skillet with Mazola oil and heat.
Make small patties and fry until crisp on both sides.
Keeps better if extra crispy.

title: crustless carrot quiche
directions: Steam cut up carrots until tender, but not mushy.
Mash a little coarsely.
Drain off any liquid.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
In large mixing bowl, mix carrots, eggs, cheese and seasonings.
Pour into pie pan or 8-inch square pan.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean and edges are slightly golden.
Cut in wedges or squares.
Quiche is best served a little warmer than room temperature or can be served cold.
Nice served with bread sticks and tossed greens.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish. Top with crackers, which have been mixed with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Pour cake mix into mixing bowl. Add sugar, eggs, oil and sour cream. Beat with mixer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into Bundt cake pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly with fingers.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Put in 1-quart jars or plastic containers.
May store in refrigerator.
Keeps 2 weeks. To bake, put in greased muffin pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°. Each quart makes 20 muffins.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in baking pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg and toss with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle on peaches.
Drizzle with butter and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and oil together until dissolved.
Pour over cucumber, onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
Let chill or eat immediately.

title: creole salad
directions: Rinse and drain cooked	macaroni.
Add and toss remaining ingredients, except
for tomatoes.	Refrigerate overnight. Add tomatoes and toss before serving.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt and water in 2-quart boiler.
Cook over high heat until mixture reaches hard ball stage.

title: john's stir-fry deer meat over rice
directions: Mix the brown sugar with the deer meat.
Let set about 20 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, soy sauce and the sesame oil.
Mix well.
Add the onions and garlic.
Let marinate in refrigerator for at least 1 hour (can be kept for 3 or 4 days in refrigerator). Stir-fry in hot pan until meat is done.
Serve over rice.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch well.
Add 1 1/4 cups boiling water and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello and red food coloring for more color.
Mix well and let cool.
Add grapefruit sections.
Pour into baked and cooled pie crust.
Add whipped cream before serving.

title: amaretto delight
directions: Line 2 pyrex dished with ice cream sandwiches.
Pour amaretto over them.
Spread a layer of cool whip over that, cover and freeze.
Before serving, toast slivered almonds and sprinkle on top of cool whip.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until creamy, then gradually add flour and vanilla.
Spread in medium size cookie sheet.
Make 3-inch square markings with knife. Spoon 1 teaspoon pie filling in each square.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Bake chicken in water until tender.
Chop mushrooms, onions, garlic and green peppers.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, bay leaf and 1 cup chicken stock.
Cook on stove top 30 minutes.
Cut chicken into pieces; combine with 1 cup stock.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Grate cheese; set aside.
Cook spaghetti as directed.
Layer in casserole the spaghetti, sauce and cheese; repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Freezes great.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: baked rice
directions: In a greased 12 oz. baking dish, combine broth, rice and parsley, salt and pepper. Cover and bake at 350 for 30 to 35 minutes or until rice is tender. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 4 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Yields 1 serving.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Combine Velveeta cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes and peppers in a crock-pot or a large saucepan and cook on low setting.
While the cheese and tomatoes are melting, cook and drain the sausage and hamburger meat.
When the cheese mixture is melted, add in the hamburger meat and sausage.
Season with cayenne pepper to taste. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with Cheddar cheese, relish, salt and garlic powder.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Shape into ball or logs and roll in desired topping.
Chill until firm and serve with crackers.

title: granny's cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour, pepper and salt.
Blend thoroughly.
Put through cookie press.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot salad
directions: Let ingredients set for a while.
Mix all together.
Very tasty.
Eat with pork rinds.
Very tasty.

title: cheese filled cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Cut off crust of bread.
Roll bread with rolling pin until very flat.
Mix Ricotta cheese with egg.
Spread 2 teaspoons Ricotta cheese on each slice of bread.
Roll up jelly roll style. Dip in butter.
Roll in cinnamon sugar.

title: white pizza
directions: Mix above ingredients; spread on muffin halves.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbly and browned.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cut each half into quarters and serve warm.

title: fruit flavor pops
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water. Pour into popsicle molds.
Freeze for 2 hours or until almost firm; insert popsicle sticks.
Freeze for 8 hours or overnight.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and place in a baking dish.
Cover with potatoes and spread soup over all.
Some water may be added from time to time throughout baking to keep moist.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Combine all ingredients until batter is smooth, but do not beat more than enough to remove lumps.
Pour into well-greased popover pan (or muffin pan).
Fill each cup 3/4 full.
Put into cold oven set at 450°; bake 30 minutes.
Don't open oven during cooking.
Makes 9.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Drain juices from cans of fruit. Whisk pudding into juices. Add fruits, including cherries. Chill before serving.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onions together.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. A double recipe makes a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift flour, Sweet 'N Low, baking powder, salt and spices into mixing bowl.
Combine egg, milk and shortening and add to dry ingredients.
Blend until flour is moistened.
Do not overmix. Batter should be lumpy.
Fold in minced apples.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups.
Pour batter 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
If baking cups are not used, grease the muffin pans.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to moderate heat (375°).
Have egg whites at room temperature.
Measure sifted flour.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; sift together 4 times.
Combine egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and flavorings in large bowl.
Beat with sturdy beater until moist peaks form.
Add rest of sugar in 4 additions, beating until blended each time.
Sift in flour mixture in 4 additions, folding in with large spoon each time.
Turn bowl often.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool cake upside-down in pan resting on cake rack.

title: eclair cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil; take off heat and add flour and eggs, one at a time.
Grease bottom of large cookie sheet and spread batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered jar.
Refrigerate three hours.
Shake before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter.
Blend in flour, garlic and pepper.
Stir in broth, milk and water.
Cook until thick.
Add chicken and soy sauce.
Pour into baking dish.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together biscuit mix, cheese and pepper.
Stir in beaten eggs just until mixture is moistened. Fold in zucchini.
In a 10-inch skillet, melt the oleo over medium heat.
Using 2 tablespoons of the mixture for each round, cook 4 rounds at a time about 2 or 3 minutes on each side or until brown.

title: granny's lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 12-inch casserole. Saute onions and bell peppers. Add ground meat and sugar; cook until meat is done. Drain. Return mixture to skillet; add tomatoes and sugar. Simmer 15 minutes. Layer meat mixture and uncooked noodles into casserole. Begin and end with meat mixture. Top with mozzarella cheese. Cover and let stand for 30 minutes. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except sweet potatoes.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add sweet potatoes and cook 15 to 20 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: cake fruit squares
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Score into 24 servings.
Drop a teaspoon of pie filling in the center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Place all items in glass cooking ware.
Mix well and bake at 350° until hot throughout.
Top with cheese and melt.
Serves 4.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook chops in hot oil with onion 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat. Stir in soup and water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chops are fork-tender, stirring occasionally. Yields 6 servings.
Prep time:
3 minutes.
Cook time:
30 minutes.

title: confederate rice with mushrooms and ham
directions: Put in large saucepan, salad oil, carrots and onions; let cook for 3 minutes.
Then add uncooked rice; blend all evenly.
Place mixture of rice, carrots and onions into a baking pan.
Add chicken stock; stir well.
Then cover with foil (be sure to cover tightly).

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine and mix well flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt. Make a well in center and add strawberries, oil and eggs.
Mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use two 4 x 8-inch loaf pans. The Birds Eye strawberries quick thaw pouches have the right amount of juice in with the strawberries.
I also cut up the strawberries smaller.

title: sara jane gilliam's franks and kraut
directions: Split franks lengthwise 2/3 deep.
Fill slit with sauerkraut. Spiral wrap each frank with 1 slice of bacon and secure with toothpick.
Grill or broil until bacon is well done.
Delicious!

title: mexican stir-fry
directions: Heat corn oil in wok or large skillet.
Add steak, onion, garlic and green pepper.
Stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender crisp.
Add picante salsa.
Stir-fry for 1 minute or until salsa is heated through.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture onto each tortilla.
Top with avocado and sour cream.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: guacamole
directions: Halve avocados; remove pits and scoop pulp into a bowl.
Add lemon juice, jalapeno, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mash coarsely with a fork.
Cover and refrigerate up to 3 hours.

title: buttermilk hot cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Beat egg until fluffy light; add milk. Gradually add to flour mixture; beat until smooth, then add melted margarine. Pour on lightly greased griddle.

title: lemon lush(3 steps)
directions: Mix together and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool completely.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix dry cake mix, egg and butter.
Pat onto pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add beaten eggs. Dissolve soda in the hot water and add to the mixture with salt and vanilla. Add flour. Roll dough quite thin. Cut with cookie cutter. Put filling in one cookie and cover with another. Seal edges with fork and prick top several times.

title: cinnamon lemon cookies
directions: In a mixer bowl, cream together sugar and butter. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, lemon peel and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Blend well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Shape dough into small balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Roll in cinnamon sugar to coat.
Set cookies 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool slightly on pans, then remove to racks to cool completely.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash thin.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Slice peppers in small rings.
Place over squash. Add chopped onion. Spoon about 2 tablespoons melted margarine over this.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread roll mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press dough against bottom.
Bake as directed for 10 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch mix, spread onto cooled dough. Spread on various raw vegetables.
Press in a little.
Sprinkle on Cheddar.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: two bean salad
directions: Drain beans and add green pepper and onion.
Set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over bean mixture.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Microwave chicken until no longer bloody (about 5 to 8 minutes).
Brown Rice-A-Roni in margarine as directed on box. Spread Rice-A-Roni in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add chicken on top of rice.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 cups water over rice and chicken.
Sprinkle flavor packet from Rice-A-Roni over chicken. Bake for about 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: pineapple and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together the sugar and flour.
Layer ingredients in order listed in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook the green beans, lima beans and peas as instructed on the packages.
Salt to taste.
Drain and mix together.
Put in 3-quart casserole.
Mix the remaining ingredients except the boiled eggs and cook for at least 5 minutes.
Put sliced eggs in and then spoon over casserole and serve.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together until nicely blended.
Add flour, a little at a time, until incorporated into butter and sugar mixture, kneading the mixture all the time.
At point when flour is fully mixed, knead another 10 to 15 minutes.
(Best to make this in cool weather.)
Cut into half (the ball of flour mix).
Flatten out onto cookie sheet about 3/4-inch thick.
Flute the edges.
Prick with a fork all over the top crust.
Preheat oven to 400°.
When the cookie sheet is put into the oven, reduce temperature to 325° and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and cut into triangles.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Put on cookie rack to cool.

title: garden salad
directions: Cut broccoli, cauliflower, carrots and celery in pieces.
Cube cheese and pepperoni.
Mix Italian dressing according to directions.
Pour over vegetables, cheese and pepperoni.
Let marinate at least 2 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pie filling and milk until very thick.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Beat until very smooth and thick.
Make layers with bananas, wafers and filling.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray with Pam a 6 x 10-inch baking pan. Stack tortillas and wrap tightly in aluminum foil.
Heat for 10 minutes.
While tortillas are heating, spread 1/3 cup picante in bottom of pan.
Combine cottage cheese, 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: punch
directions: Combine jello, Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add 8 cups boiling water. Stir until dissolved.
Add ReaLemon and pineapple juice; stir.
Add 1 gallon cold water.
Put into (1 gallon) containers.
Be sure they have wide openings.
Freeze.

title: chicken cacciatore a la forgia
directions: In a little olive oil, brown chicken.
Add tomatoes, garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Cook at a simmer at least one hour. The longer, the better!
Serve on a bed or rice.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add the cold water, Hi-C and lemon juice.

title: creamy vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put in refrigerator.
Chill overnight.
Take out 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: chokecherry jelly
directions: Measure juice into a large saucepan.
Add pectin and stir well.
Bring to a hard boil.
Add sugar, stir until dissolved. Bring to a rolling boil and boil hard for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, skim, and pour into hot sterilized jars.
Cover with melted paraffin or seal.

title: orange jello cake
directions: Mix water and jello to dissolve.
Mix cake, eggs and oil. Slowly beat in jello.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Mix the orange juice and powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour over cake; return to oven for about 5 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix together the sugar, Hershey's cocoa, Karo and milk in a pan.
Boil at a rolling boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from stove; set pan in cold water.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Beat with electric beaters until it starts to thicken.
Beat until thicker for fudge.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients with electric mixer until stiff. Fold in fruit cocktail and chopped nuts.
Serve on sliced angel food cake and top with a cherry.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: fried turkey
directions: Having thawed your turkey, remove all wrappings, neck and giblets.
Cover the turkey, inside and out, with seasonings.
Use paprika last.
Place turkey in plastic bag and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: turkey parmesan
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix soup with vegetables and turkey in a casserole.
Add noodles and seasonings and mix thoroughly. Sprinkle the cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Arrange butter on top of the crumbs in small pats.
Cook in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until crumbs are crusty on top.
This is delicious!

title: round steak and gravy
directions: Steak should be cut in serving pieces.
Salt and pepper. Place in bottom of crock-pot.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over all. Cook on low for 8 hours, or high for 4 to 6 hours.
Makes perfect brown gravy.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes for 1 hour at 350°.
Cut potatoes into half lengthwise and then spoon out.
Mix potatoes with other ingredients and refill potato shells.
Mix with paprika.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: salmon-corn chowder
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Flake salmon and mash round bones.
Saute onion and celery in butter in large saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in flour.
Add bouillon cubes, water and potatoes.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add salmon, including liquid, bones and skin.
Stir in milk, corn, dill weed, salt and black pepper to taste.
Heat well.

title: punch for kids
directions: Mix and serve with a spoon of sherbet.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar, milk and peanut butter.
Fold in beaten heavy cream; add to mixture.
Swirl hot fudge topping with a knife into mixture.
Freeze.

title: mabel (dodge) kerr's sour cream raisin bars
directions: Cook raisins in 1 cup water for 10 minutes.
Drain and cool. Mix together brown sugar, margarine, oatmeal, soda and flour.
Put half this mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix egg yolks, sour cream, sugar and cornstarch and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add raisins and vanilla.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle remaining oatmeal mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: In large bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add yolks and honey; beat well.
Stir in milk, rum and vanilla. Chill.
Just before serving, fold in whipped cream and pour into glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: wild rice
directions: Mix rice, peppers, celery, onion and chicken broth and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Add cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms, and almonds.
Bake 40 more minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and set in refrigerator.
Mix the last 3 ingredients well. When Jell-O mixture partially sets, combine pineapple mixture. Stir well and place in refrigerator to set.

title: smoked salmon with sauce
directions: Entice hubby
to
smoke whole salmon on smoker.
Chill. Whisk together the
sauce
in the order given.
Marinate a few hours to improve flavor.
Can thin with vinegar, if needed.

title: aunt mary's chocolate gravy
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa. Add milk. Cook until thick. Add butter and vanilla. Delicious over hot biscuits.

title: congo bars
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and eggs in large bowl.
Mix well.
Line baking pan with 1 package Pillsbury cookie dough, sliced.
Make sure dough is close together.
Fill with cream cheese and top with second package Pillsbury dough, sliced.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomatoes, in bowl.
Make a tomato bowl by cutting through the tomato 3 times to the bottom core. Spread open the tomato; spoon in tuna salad.
Serves 2.
Serve with unsalted crackers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture fills 3 small frozen pie shells or two deep dishes.
When baked, cool and spread Cool Whip topping on each.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar with beater until well blended. Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: jenne's pecan pie bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and blend well.

Spread firmly over bottom and sides of an ungreased 7 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven. Combine remaining ingredients and blend well. Spread over baked crust. Return to oven and bake for 15 more minutes. Remove from oven and cool. Cut into bars.

title: dove and wild rice dressing
directions: Combine
flour,
salt, pepper and paprika in brown bag. Add dove; shake.
Brown in shortening in iron skillet or other type. Remove.
Place
in circle in casserole.
Wash rice; add boiling water.
Cook until water is absorbed.

title: "candied" sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash apricots and soak with raisins in apple juice for 1 hour.
Steam sweet potatoes until tender.
In a small saucepan, combine tapioca with apricots, raisins and juice. Let mixture stand for 5 minutes.
Bring to boil over medium heat; stir often.
Remove from heat.
Add brandy (optional) and cool for 20 minutes.
Cut cooked sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix with applesauce.
Place this mixture in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Pour the apricot-raisin sauce over the top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dip for fresh fruit
directions: Mix all together with mixer.

title: spinach stuffed mushrooms
directions: In small skillet heat margarine until bubbly.
Chop up mushroom stems and onions, put in margarine until margarine is soaked up by onions and mushroom stems.
Add cooked spinach, rice, cheese (grated works best), salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese melts. Stuff large mushrooms.
Place mushrooms in pan and add broth to bottom of pan.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: pasta sauce with mortadella and green peas
directions: Melt the butter and heat the oil in a saucepan.
Add Prosciutto, asparagus, mushrooms, carrot and zucchini.
Stir. Cover and cook over moderate flame for 5 minutes.
Add the onions, peas, basil, salt and pepper.
Increase heat until mixture boils. Then reduce to simmer and cook, covered, another 4 to 5 minutes. Pour mixture over hot pasta and mix gently.
Sprinkle with parsley and grated cheese.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: butterscotch coconut squares
directions: Cook butter and brown sugar until bubbly.
Beat eggs; add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add brown sugar mixture. Add coconut and nuts.
Pour in 12 x 7-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: double boiler bread pudding
directions: Put brown sugar in top of double boiler.
Cut up 3 to 4 slices of bread in squares.
Put on top of brown sugar.
Then beat eggs. Stir into milk and vanilla.
Pour over the bread and sugar.
Don't stir.
Cook over water slowly for about 1 1/2 hours.
When done the sugar forms a syrup in the bottom of mixture.
Very easy and good to make.

title: puppy dog trash
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in microwave.
Put cereal in bowl; pour melted ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Put powdered sugar in paper bag; add cereal mixture and shake bag well.
Put in airtight container to store.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, peanuts and salt in a 2-quart casserole dish. Stir well. Microwave on High 8 to 9 minutes.
Mixture will be light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly. Microwave on High 1 to 3 minutes until mixture reaches hard crack stage.
Stir in soda quickly.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet. Cool 1 hour. Break. Store in airtight container.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Combine cake mix with applesauce, eggs and flavoring.
Mix well.
In another pan, toss nuts and fruit with flour to coat. Stir fruit and nuts in cake mixture; mix well.
Put mixture in a Bundt cake pan or in two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 250° for about 1 3/4 hours or until cake test is done.
Take from oven and pour wine over cake and wrap immediately with plastic wrap.

title: asparagus cheese casserole(lo-cal)
directions: Melt oleo; stir in flour.
When smooth, slowly add milk and salt.
Continue cooking and stirring until thick (making a sauce). Layer asparagus, eggs, pimento, cheese, onion flakes and sauce; repeat for second layer and sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 (about 80 calories per serving).

title: buffet green beans
directions: Cook bacon and onion in large skillet over medium heat, stirring often, until bacon is crisp. Remove bacon and onion with slotted spoon, reserving 1/4-cup drippings in pan. Drain bacon and onions on paper towels; set aside. Combine sugar and vinegar; pour into reserved drippings and bring to a boil. Add beans; cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. Spoon into a serving dish; top with bacon and onions. Yield: 8 servings.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix together all at once.
Chill.
Roll into 1 to 2-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; beat with mixer.
Add coloring.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Beat after each addition on medium speed.
Add vanilla; mix and stir in last, without beating the vinegar, with soda dissolved in it.
Pour into 3 round 8-inch pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: Combine and cook in large soup pot.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: rhubarb meringue pie
directions: Place rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Beat egg yolks, flour and margarine together.
Slowly stir in milk.
Add sugar and lemon juice, mixing well.
Beat the 2 egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour over the rhubarb.
Bake in 450° oven 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 to 45 minutes longer. This pie does not need a top crust as the egg whites make a delicious topping.

title: pumpkin spice bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first six ingredients; set flour mixture aside.
Combine pumpkin and applesauce; set aside. Beat sugar and margarine in a large bowl at medium speed of a mixer until well blended (5 minutes).

Add egg whites and vanilla, beat well.	Add flour mixture to sugar mixture mixing alternately with pumpkin mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Pour batter into 12 cup bundt pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake for 50 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.

Cool cake in pan for ten minutes, then remove from pan.	Combine brown sugar, rum and milk in a small saucepan; cook over low heat until brown sugar has dissolved.	Remove sugar mixture from heat and add powdered sugar stirring with a whisk.
Spoon glaze over warm cake.

title: rockport red sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Serve with fried seafood or salad.
Makes about 1 pint.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix salad dressing and juice.
Dice unpeeled apples.
Mix with celery and nuts.
Fold in dressing.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cranberry banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and blend.
Add flour, baking soda, nuts and bananas.
Blend well.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes at 325° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Better the next day.
Freezes well.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and jam.
Beat thoroughly. Sift flour, measure and sift with baking soda, salt and spices. Add alternately with milk to first mixture, beat thoroughly.
Pour into well-oiled pan.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.
Use brown sugar icing.
